68static void determineDirectionality(TextDirection& dir, InlineIterator iter)
69{
70 while (!iter.atEnd()) {
71 if (iter.atParagraphSeparator())
72 return;
73 if (UChar current = iter.current()) {
74 UCharDirection charDirection = u_charDirection(current);
75 if (charDirection == U_LEFT_TO_RIGHT) {
76 dir = TextDirection::LTR;
77 return;
78 }
79 if (charDirection == U_RIGHT_TO_LEFT || charDirection == U_RIGHT_TO_LEFT_ARABIC) {
80 dir = TextDirection::RTL;
81 return;
82 }
83 }
84 iter.increment();
85 }
86}

93void LegacyLineLayout::appendRunsForObject(BidiRunList<BidiRun>* runs, int start, int end, RenderObject& obj, InlineBidiResolver& resolver)
94{
95 if (start > end || RenderBlock::shouldSkipCreatingRunsForObject(obj))
96 return;
97
98 LineWhitespaceCollapsingState& lineWhitespaceCollapsingState = resolver.whitespaceCollapsingState();
99 bool haveNextTransition = (lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.currentTransition() < lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.numTransitions());
100 InlineIterator nextTransition;
101 if (haveNextTransition)
102 nextTransition = lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.transitions()[lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.currentTransition()];
103 if (lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.betweenTransitions()) {
104 if (!haveNextTransition || (&obj != nextTransition.renderer()))
105 return;
106 // This is a new start point. Stop ignoring objects and
107 // adjust our start.
108 start = nextTransition.offset();
109 lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.incrementCurrentTransition();
110 if (start < end) {
111 appendRunsForObject(runs, start, end, obj, resolver);
112 return;
113 }
114 } else {
115 if (!haveNextTransition || (&obj != nextTransition.renderer())) {
116 if (runs)
117 runs->appendRun(createRun(start, end, obj, resolver));
118 return;
119 }
120
121 // An end transition has been encountered within our object. We need to append a run with our endpoint.
122 if (static_cast<int>(nextTransition.offset() + 1) <= end) {
123 lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.incrementCurrentTransition();
124 // The end of the line is before the object we're inspecting. Skip everything and return
125 if (nextTransition.refersToEndOfPreviousNode())
126 return;
127 if (static_cast<int>(nextTransition.offset() + 1) > start && runs)
128 runs->appendRun(createRun(start, nextTransition.offset() + 1, obj, resolver));
129 appendRunsForObject(runs, nextTransition.offset() + 1, end, obj, resolver);
130 } else if (runs)
131 runs->appendRun(createRun(start, end, obj, resolver));
132 }
133}

135std::unique_ptr<LegacyRootInlineBox> LegacyLineLayout::createRootInlineBox()
136{
137 if (is<RenderSVGText>(m_flow)) {
138 auto box = makeUnique<SVGRootInlineBox>(downcast<RenderSVGText>(m_flow));
139 box->setHasVirtualLogicalHeight();
140 return box;
141 }
142
143 return makeUnique<LegacyRootInlineBox>(m_flow);
144}

146LegacyRootInlineBox* LegacyLineLayout::createAndAppendRootInlineBox()
147{
148 auto newRootBox = createRootInlineBox();
149 LegacyRootInlineBox* rootBox = newRootBox.get();
150 m_lineBoxes.appendLineBox(WTFMove(newRootBox));
151
152 if (UNLIKELY(AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) && firstRootBox() == rootBox) {
153 if (AXObjectCache* cache = m_flow.document().existingAXObjectCache())
154 cache->deferRecomputeIsIgnored(m_flow.element());
155 }
156
157 return rootBox;
158}

160LegacyInlineBox* LegacyLineLayout::createInlineBoxForRenderer(RenderObject* renderer, bool isOnlyRun)
161{
162 if (renderer == &m_flow)
163 return createAndAppendRootInlineBox();
164
165 if (is<RenderText>(*renderer))
166 return downcast<RenderText>(*renderer).createInlineTextBox();
167
168 if (is<RenderBox>(*renderer)) {
169 // FIXME: This is terrible. This branch returns an *owned* pointer!
170 return downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).createInlineBox().release();
171 }
172
173 if (is<RenderLineBreak>(*renderer)) {
174 // FIXME: This is terrible. This branch returns an *owned* pointer!
175 auto inlineBox = downcast<RenderLineBreak>(*renderer).createInlineBox().release();
176 // We only treat a box as text for a <br> if we are on a line by ourself or in strict mode
177 // (Note the use of strict mode. In "almost strict" mode, we don't treat the box for <br> as text.)
178 inlineBox->setBehavesLikeText(isOnlyRun || renderer->document().inNoQuirksMode() || renderer->isLineBreakOpportunity());
179 return inlineBox;
180 }
181
182 return downcast<RenderInline>(*renderer).createAndAppendInlineFlowBox();
183}

185static inline void dirtyLineBoxesForRenderer(RenderObject& renderer, bool fullLayout)
186{
187 if (is<RenderText>(renderer)) {
188 RenderText& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(renderer);
189 updateCounterIfNeeded(renderText);
190 renderText.dirtyLineBoxes(fullLayout);
191 } else if (is<RenderLineBreak>(renderer))
192 downcast<RenderLineBreak>(renderer).dirtyLineBoxes(fullLayout);
193 else
194 downcast<RenderInline>(renderer).dirtyLineBoxes(fullLayout);
195}

197static bool parentIsConstructedOrHaveNext(LegacyInlineFlowBox* parentBox)
198{
199 do {
200 if (parentBox->isConstructed() || parentBox->nextOnLine())
201 return true;
202 parentBox = parentBox->parent();
203 } while (parentBox);
204 return false;
205}
206
207LegacyInlineFlowBox* LegacyLineLayout::createLineBoxes(RenderObject* obj, const LineInfo& lineInfo, LegacyInlineBox* childBox)
208{
209 // See if we have an unconstructed line box for this object that is also
210 // the last item on the line.
211 unsigned lineDepth = 1;
212 LegacyInlineFlowBox* parentBox = nullptr;
213 LegacyInlineFlowBox* result = nullptr;
214 bool hasDefaultLineBoxContain = style().lineBoxContain() == RenderStyle::initialLineBoxContain();
215 do {
216 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(is<RenderInline>(*obj) || obj == &m_flow);
217
218 RenderInline* inlineFlow = obj != &m_flow ? downcast<RenderInline>(obj) : nullptr;
219
220 // Get the last box we made for this render object.
221 parentBox = inlineFlow ? inlineFlow->lastLineBox() : downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*obj).lastRootBox();
222
223 // If this box or its ancestor is constructed then it is from a previous line, and we need
224 // to make a new box for our line. If this box or its ancestor is unconstructed but it has
225 // something following it on the line, then we know we have to make a new box
226 // as well. In this situation our inline has actually been split in two on
227 // the same line (this can happen with very fancy language mixtures).
228 bool constructedNewBox = false;
229 bool allowedToConstructNewBox = !hasDefaultLineBoxContain || !inlineFlow || inlineFlow->alwaysCreateLineBoxes();
230 bool canUseExistingParentBox = parentBox && !parentIsConstructedOrHaveNext(parentBox);
231 if (allowedToConstructNewBox && !canUseExistingParentBox) {
232 // We need to make a new box for this render object. Once
233 // made, we need to place it at the end of the current line.
234 LegacyInlineBox* newBox = createInlineBoxForRenderer(obj);
235 parentBox = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(newBox);
236 parentBox->setIsFirstLine(lineInfo.isFirstLine());
237 parentBox->setIsHorizontal(m_flow.isHorizontalWritingMode());
238 if (!hasDefaultLineBoxContain)
239 parentBox->clearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline();
240 constructedNewBox = true;
241 }
242
243 if (constructedNewBox || canUseExistingParentBox) {
244 if (!result)
245 result = parentBox;
246
247 // If we have hit the block itself, then |box| represents the root
248 // inline box for the line, and it doesn't have to be appended to any parent
249 // inline.
250 if (childBox)
251 parentBox->addToLine(childBox);
252
253 if (!constructedNewBox || obj == &m_flow)
254 break;
255
256 childBox = parentBox;
257 }
258
259 // If we've exceeded our line depth, then jump straight to the root and skip all the remaining
260 // intermediate inline flows.
261 obj = (++lineDepth >= cMaxLineDepth) ? &m_flow : obj->parent();
262
263 } while (true);
264
265 return result;
266}

268template<typename CharacterType> static inline bool endsWithHTMLSpaces(const CharacterType* characters, unsigned position, unsigned end)
269{
270 for (unsigned i = position; i < end; ++i) {
271 if (!isHTMLSpace(characters[i]))
272 return false;
273 }
274 return true;
275}
276
277static bool reachedEndOfTextRenderer(const BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns)
278{
279 BidiRun* run = bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun();
280 if (!run)
281 return true;
282 if (!is<RenderText>(run->renderer()))
283 return false;
284 auto& text = downcast<RenderText>(run->renderer()).text();
285 unsigned position = run->stop();
286 unsigned length = text.length();
287 if (text.is8Bit())
288 return endsWithHTMLSpaces(text.characters8(), position, length);
289 return endsWithHTMLSpaces(text.characters16(), position, length);
290}

292LegacyRootInlineBox* LegacyLineLayout::constructLine(BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns, const LineInfo& lineInfo)
293{
294 ASSERT(bidiRuns.firstRun());
295
296 LegacyInlineFlowBox* parentBox = 0;
297 int runCount = bidiRuns.runCount() - lineInfo.runsFromLeadingWhitespace();
298
299 for (BidiRun* r = bidiRuns.firstRun(); r; r = r->next()) {
300 // Create a box for our object.
301 bool isOnlyRun = (runCount == 1);
302 if (runCount == 2 && !r->renderer().isListMarker())
303 isOnlyRun = (!style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? bidiRuns.lastRun() : bidiRuns.firstRun())->renderer().isListMarker();
304
305 if (lineInfo.isEmpty())
306 continue;
307
308 LegacyInlineBox* box = createInlineBoxForRenderer(&r->renderer(), isOnlyRun);
309 r->setBox(box);
310
311 // If we have no parent box yet, or if the run is not simply a sibling,
312 // then we need to construct inline boxes as necessary to properly enclose the
313 // run's inline box. Segments can only be siblings at the root level, as
314 // they are positioned separately.
315 if (!parentBox || &parentBox->renderer() != r->renderer().parent()) {
316 // Create new inline boxes all the way back to the appropriate insertion point.
317 RenderObject* parentToUse = r->renderer().parent();
318 parentBox = createLineBoxes(parentToUse, lineInfo, box);
319 } else {
320 // Append the inline box to this line.
321 parentBox->addToLine(box);
322 }
323
324 bool visuallyOrdered = r->renderer().style().rtlOrdering() == Order::Visual;
325 box->setBidiLevel(r->level());
326
327 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*box)) {
328 auto& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*box);
329 textBox.setStart(r->m_start);
330 textBox.setLen(r->m_stop - r->m_start);
331 textBox.setDirOverride(r->dirOverride(visuallyOrdered));
332 if (r->m_hasHyphen)
333 textBox.setHasHyphen(true);
334 }
335 }
336
337 // We should have a root inline box. It should be unconstructed and
338 // be the last continuation of our line list.
339 ASSERT(lastRootBox() && !lastRootBox()->isConstructed());
340
341 // Set bits on our inline flow boxes that indicate which sides should
342 // paint borders/margins/padding. This knowledge will ultimately be used when
343 // we determine the horizontal positions and widths of all the inline boxes on
344 // the line.
345 bool isLogicallyLastRunWrapped = bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->renderer().isText() ? !reachedEndOfTextRenderer(bidiRuns) : !is<RenderInline>(bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->renderer());
346 lastRootBox()->determineSpacingForFlowBoxes(lineInfo.isLastLine(), isLogicallyLastRunWrapped, &bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->renderer());
347
348 // Now mark the line boxes as being constructed.
349 lastRootBox()->setConstructed();
350
351 // Return the last line.
352 return lastRootBox();
353}

355TextAlignMode LegacyLineLayout::textAlignmentForLine(bool endsWithSoftBreak) const
356{
357 if (auto overrideAlignment = m_flow.overrideTextAlignmentForLine(endsWithSoftBreak))
358 return *overrideAlignment;
359
360 TextAlignMode alignment = style().textAlign();
361#if ENABLE(CSS3_TEXT)
362 TextJustify textJustify = style().textJustify();
363 if (alignment == TextAlignMode::Justify && textJustify == TextJustify::None)
364 return style().direction() == TextDirection::LTR ? TextAlignMode::Left : TextAlignMode::Right;
365#endif
366
367 if (endsWithSoftBreak)
368 return alignment;
369
370#if !ENABLE(CSS3_TEXT)
371 return (alignment == TextAlignMode::Justify) ? TextAlignMode::Start : alignment;
372#else
373 if (alignment != TextAlignMode::Justify)
374 return alignment;
375
376 TextAlignLast alignmentLast = style().textAlignLast();
377 switch (alignmentLast) {
378 case TextAlignLast::Start:
379 return TextAlignMode::Start;
380 case TextAlignLast::End:
381 return TextAlignMode::End;
382 case TextAlignLast::Left:
383 return TextAlignMode::Left;
384 case TextAlignLast::Right:
385 return TextAlignMode::Right;
386 case TextAlignLast::Center:
387 return TextAlignMode::Center;
388 case TextAlignLast::Justify:
389 return TextAlignMode::Justify;
390 case TextAlignLast::Auto:
391 if (textJustify == TextJustify::Distribute)
392 return TextAlignMode::Justify;
393 return TextAlignMode::Start;
394 }
395 return alignment;
396#endif
397}

399static void updateLogicalWidthForLeftAlignedBlock(bool isLeftToRightDirection, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, float& logicalLeft, float& totalLogicalWidth, float availableLogicalWidth)
400{
401 // The direction of the block should determine what happens with wide lines.
402 // In particular with RTL blocks, wide lines should still spill out to the left.
403 if (isLeftToRightDirection) {
404 if (totalLogicalWidth > availableLogicalWidth && trailingSpaceRun)
405 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(std::max<float>(0, trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth() - totalLogicalWidth + availableLogicalWidth));
406 return;
407 }
408
409 if (trailingSpaceRun)
410 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(0);
411 else if (totalLogicalWidth > availableLogicalWidth)
412 logicalLeft -= (totalLogicalWidth - availableLogicalWidth);
413}
414
415static void updateLogicalWidthForRightAlignedBlock(bool isLeftToRightDirection, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, float& logicalLeft, float& totalLogicalWidth, float availableLogicalWidth)
416{
417 // Wide lines spill out of the block based off direction.
418 // So even if text-align is right, if direction is LTR, wide lines should overflow out of the right
419 // side of the block.
420 if (isLeftToRightDirection) {
421 if (trailingSpaceRun) {
422 totalLogicalWidth -= trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth();
423 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(0);
424 }
425 logicalLeft += std::max(0.f, availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth);
426 return;
427 }
428
429 if (totalLogicalWidth > availableLogicalWidth && trailingSpaceRun) {
430 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(std::max<float>(0, trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth() - totalLogicalWidth + availableLogicalWidth));
431 totalLogicalWidth -= trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth();
432 } else
433 logicalLeft += availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth;
434}
435
436static void updateLogicalWidthForCenterAlignedBlock(bool isLeftToRightDirection, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, float& logicalLeft, float& totalLogicalWidth, float availableLogicalWidth)
437{
438 float trailingSpaceWidth = 0;
439 if (trailingSpaceRun) {
440 totalLogicalWidth -= trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth();
441 trailingSpaceWidth = std::min(trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth(), (availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth + 1) / 2);
442 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(std::max<float>(0, trailingSpaceWidth));
443 }
444 if (isLeftToRightDirection)
445 logicalLeft += std::max<float>((availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth) / 2, 0);
446 else
447 logicalLeft += totalLogicalWidth > availableLogicalWidth ? (availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth) : (availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth) / 2 - trailingSpaceWidth;
448}

450void LegacyLineLayout::setMarginsForRubyRun(BidiRun* run, RenderRubyRun& renderer, RenderObject* previousObject, const LineInfo& lineInfo)
451{
452 float startOverhang;
453 float endOverhang;
454 RenderObject* nextObject = 0;
455 for (BidiRun* runWithNextObject = run->next(); runWithNextObject; runWithNextObject = runWithNextObject->next()) {
456 if (!runWithNextObject->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !runWithNextObject->box()->isLineBreak()) {
457 nextObject = &runWithNextObject->renderer();
458 break;
459 }
460 }
461 renderer.getOverhang(lineInfo.isFirstLine(), renderer.style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? previousObject : nextObject, renderer.style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? nextObject : previousObject, startOverhang, endOverhang);
462 m_flow.setMarginStartForChild(renderer, LayoutUnit(-startOverhang));
463 m_flow.setMarginEndForChild(renderer, LayoutUnit(-endOverhang));
464}

466static inline void setLogicalWidthForTextRun(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox, BidiRun* run, RenderText& renderer, float xPos, const LineInfo& lineInfo,
467 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache, WordMeasurements& wordMeasurements)
468{
469 HashSet<const Font*> fallbackFonts;
470 GlyphOverflow glyphOverflow;
471
472 const FontCascade& font = lineStyle(*renderer.parent(), lineInfo).fontCascade();
473 // Always compute glyph overflow if the block's line-box-contain value is "glyphs".
474 if (lineBox->fitsToGlyphs()) {
475 // If we don't stick out of the root line's font box, then don't bother computing our glyph overflow. This optimization
476 // will keep us from computing glyph bounds in nearly all cases.
477 bool includeRootLine = lineBox->includesRootLineBoxFontOrLeading();
478 int baselineShift = lineBox->verticalPositionForBox(run->box(), verticalPositionCache);
479 int rootDescent = includeRootLine ? font.fontMetrics().descent() : 0;
480 int rootAscent = includeRootLine ? font.fontMetrics().ascent() : 0;
481 int boxAscent = font.fontMetrics().ascent() - baselineShift;
482 int boxDescent = font.fontMetrics().descent() + baselineShift;
483 if (boxAscent > rootDescent || boxDescent > rootAscent)
484 glyphOverflow.computeBounds = true;
485 }
486
487 LayoutUnit hyphenWidth;
488 if (downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*run->box()).hasHyphen())
489 hyphenWidth = measureHyphenWidth(renderer, font, &fallbackFonts);
490
491 float measuredWidth = 0;
492
493 bool kerningIsEnabled = font.enableKerning();
494 bool canUseSimpleFontCodePath = renderer.canUseSimpleFontCodePath();
495
496 // Since we don't cache glyph overflows, we need to re-measure the run if
497 // the style is linebox-contain: glyph.
498 if (!lineBox->fitsToGlyphs() && canUseSimpleFontCodePath) {
499 unsigned lastEndOffset = run->m_start;
500 bool atFirstWordMeasurement = true;
501 for (size_t i = 0, size = wordMeasurements.size(); i < size && lastEndOffset < run->m_stop; ++i) {
502 WordMeasurement& wordMeasurement = wordMeasurements[i];
503 if (wordMeasurement.width <= 0 || wordMeasurement.startOffset == wordMeasurement.endOffset)
504 continue;
505 if (wordMeasurement.renderer != &renderer || wordMeasurement.startOffset != lastEndOffset || wordMeasurement.endOffset > run->m_stop)
506 continue;
507
508 lastEndOffset = wordMeasurement.endOffset;
509 if (kerningIsEnabled && lastEndOffset == run->m_stop) {
510 int wordLength = lastEndOffset - wordMeasurement.startOffset;
511 GlyphOverflow overflow;
512 measuredWidth += renderer.width(wordMeasurement.startOffset, wordLength, xPos + measuredWidth, lineInfo.isFirstLine(),
513 &wordMeasurement.fallbackFonts, &overflow);
514 UChar c = renderer.characterAt(wordMeasurement.startOffset);
515 // renderer.width() omits word-spacing value for leading whitespace, so let's just add it back here.
516 if (!atFirstWordMeasurement && FontCascade::treatAsSpace(c))
517 measuredWidth += renderer.style().fontCascade().wordSpacing();
518 } else
519 measuredWidth += wordMeasurement.width;
520 atFirstWordMeasurement = false;
521
522 for (auto& font : wordMeasurement.fallbackFonts)
523 fallbackFonts.add(font);
524 }
525 if (measuredWidth && lastEndOffset != run->m_stop) {
526 // If we don't have enough cached data, we'll measure the run again.
527 measuredWidth = 0;
528 fallbackFonts.clear();
529 }
530 }
531
532 if (!measuredWidth)
533 measuredWidth = renderer.width(run->m_start, run->m_stop - run->m_start, xPos, lineInfo.isFirstLine(), &fallbackFonts, &glyphOverflow);
534
535 ASSERT(measuredWidth >= 0);
536 ASSERT(hyphenWidth >= 0);
537
538 run->box()->setLogicalWidth(measuredWidth + hyphenWidth);
539 if (!fallbackFonts.isEmpty()) {
540 ASSERT(run->box()->behavesLikeText());
541 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap::iterator it = textBoxDataMap.add(downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(run->box()), std::make_pair(Vector<const Font*>(), GlyphOverflow())).iterator;
542 ASSERT(it->value.first.isEmpty());
543 it->value.first = copyToVector(fallbackFonts);
544 run->box()->parent()->clearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline();
545 }
546
547 // Include text decoration visual overflow as part of the glyph overflow.
548 if (!renderer.style().textDecorationsInEffect().isEmpty())
549 glyphOverflow.extendTo(visualOverflowForDecorations(run->box()->lineStyle(), downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(run->box())));
550
551 if (!glyphOverflow.isEmpty()) {
552 ASSERT(run->box()->behavesLikeText());
553 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap::iterator it = textBoxDataMap.add(downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(run->box()), std::make_pair(Vector<const Font*>(), GlyphOverflow())).iterator;
554 it->value.second = glyphOverflow;
555 run->box()->clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
556 }
557}

559void LegacyLineLayout::updateRubyForJustifiedText(RenderRubyRun& rubyRun, BidiRun& r, const Vector<unsigned, 16>& expansionOpportunities, unsigned& expansionOpportunityCount, float& totalLogicalWidth, float availableLogicalWidth, size_t& i)
560{
561 if (!rubyRun.rubyBase() || !rubyRun.rubyBase()->firstRootBox() || rubyRun.rubyBase()->firstRootBox()->nextRootBox() || !r.renderer().style().collapseWhiteSpace())
562 return;
563
564 auto& rubyBase = *rubyRun.rubyBase();
565 auto& rootBox = *rubyBase.firstRootBox();
566
567 float totalExpansion = 0;
568 unsigned totalOpportunitiesInRun = 0;
569 for (auto* leafChild = rootBox.firstLeafDescendant(); leafChild; leafChild = leafChild->nextLeafOnLine()) {
570 if (!leafChild->isInlineTextBox())
571 continue;
572
573 unsigned opportunitiesInRun = expansionOpportunities[i++];
574 ASSERT(opportunitiesInRun <= expansionOpportunityCount);
575 auto expansion = (availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth) * opportunitiesInRun / expansionOpportunityCount;
576 totalExpansion += expansion;
577 totalOpportunitiesInRun += opportunitiesInRun;
578 }
579
580 ASSERT(!rubyRun.hasOverridingLogicalWidth());
581 float newBaseWidth = rubyRun.logicalWidth() + totalExpansion + m_flow.marginStartForChild(rubyRun) + m_flow.marginEndForChild(rubyRun);
582 float newRubyRunWidth = rubyRun.logicalWidth() + totalExpansion;
583 rubyBase.setInitialOffset((newRubyRunWidth - newBaseWidth) / 2);
584 rubyRun.setOverridingLogicalWidth(LayoutUnit(newRubyRunWidth));
585 rubyRun.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
586 rootBox.markDirty();
587 if (RenderRubyText* rubyText = rubyRun.rubyText()) {
588 if (LegacyRootInlineBox* textRootBox = rubyText->firstRootBox())
589 textRootBox->markDirty();
590 }
591 rubyRun.layoutBlock(true);
592 rubyRun.clearOverridingLogicalWidth();
593 r.box()->setExpansion(newRubyRunWidth - r.box()->logicalWidth());
594
595 totalLogicalWidth += totalExpansion;
596 expansionOpportunityCount -= totalOpportunitiesInRun;
597}
598
599void LegacyLineLayout::computeExpansionForJustifiedText(BidiRun* firstRun, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, const Vector<unsigned, 16>& expansionOpportunities, unsigned expansionOpportunityCount, float totalLogicalWidth, float availableLogicalWidth)
600{
601 if (!expansionOpportunityCount || availableLogicalWidth <= totalLogicalWidth)
602 return;
603
604 size_t i = 0;
605 for (BidiRun* run = firstRun; run; run = run->next()) {
606 if (!run->box() || run == trailingSpaceRun)
607 continue;
608
609 if (is<RenderText>(run->renderer())) {
610 unsigned opportunitiesInRun = expansionOpportunities[i++];
611
612 ASSERT(opportunitiesInRun <= expansionOpportunityCount);
613
614 // Only justify text if whitespace is collapsed.
615 if (run->renderer().style().collapseWhiteSpace()) {
616 LegacyInlineTextBox& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*run->box());
617 float expansion = (availableLogicalWidth - totalLogicalWidth) * opportunitiesInRun / expansionOpportunityCount;
618 textBox.setExpansion(expansion);
619 totalLogicalWidth += expansion;
620 }
621 expansionOpportunityCount -= opportunitiesInRun;
622 } else if (is<RenderRubyRun>(run->renderer()))
623 updateRubyForJustifiedText(downcast<RenderRubyRun>(run->renderer()), *run, expansionOpportunities, expansionOpportunityCount, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, i);
624
625 if (!expansionOpportunityCount)
626 break;
627 }
628}
629
630void LegacyLineLayout::updateLogicalWidthForAlignment(RenderBlockFlow& flow, const TextAlignMode& textAlign, const LegacyRootInlineBox* rootInlineBox, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, float& logicalLeft, float& totalLogicalWidth, float& availableLogicalWidth, int expansionOpportunityCount)
631{
632 TextDirection direction;
633 if (rootInlineBox && flow.style().unicodeBidi() == Plaintext)
634 direction = rootInlineBox->direction();
635 else
636 direction = flow.style().direction();
637
638 bool isLeftToRightDirection = flow.style().isLeftToRightDirection();
639
640 // Armed with the total width of the line (without justification),
641 // we now examine our text-align property in order to determine where to position the
642 // objects horizontally. The total width of the line can be increased if we end up
643 // justifying text.
644 switch (textAlign) {
645 case TextAlignMode::Left:
646 case TextAlignMode::WebKitLeft:
647 updateLogicalWidthForLeftAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
648 break;
649 case TextAlignMode::Right:
650 case TextAlignMode::WebKitRight:
651 updateLogicalWidthForRightAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
652 break;
653 case TextAlignMode::Center:
654 case TextAlignMode::WebKitCenter:
655 updateLogicalWidthForCenterAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
656 break;
657 case TextAlignMode::Justify:
658 flow.adjustInlineDirectionLineBounds(expansionOpportunityCount, logicalLeft, availableLogicalWidth);
659 if (expansionOpportunityCount) {
660 if (trailingSpaceRun) {
661 totalLogicalWidth -= trailingSpaceRun->box()->logicalWidth();
662 trailingSpaceRun->box()->setLogicalWidth(0);
663 }
664 break;
665 }
666 FALLTHROUGH;
667 case TextAlignMode::Start:
668 if (direction == TextDirection::LTR)
669 updateLogicalWidthForLeftAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
670 else
671 updateLogicalWidthForRightAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
672 break;
673 case TextAlignMode::End:
674 if (direction == TextDirection::LTR)
675 updateLogicalWidthForRightAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
676 else
677 updateLogicalWidthForLeftAlignedBlock(isLeftToRightDirection, trailingSpaceRun, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
678 break;
679 }
680}
681
682static void updateLogicalInlinePositions(RenderBlockFlow& block, float& lineLogicalLeft, float& lineLogicalRight, float& availableLogicalWidth, bool firstLine,
683 IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText, LayoutUnit boxLogicalHeight)
684{
685 LayoutUnit lineLogicalHeight = block.minLineHeightForReplacedRenderer(firstLine, boxLogicalHeight);
686 lineLogicalLeft = block.logicalLeftOffsetForLine(block.logicalHeight(), shouldIndentText, lineLogicalHeight);
687 lineLogicalRight = block.logicalRightOffsetForLine(block.logicalHeight(), shouldIndentText, lineLogicalHeight);
688 availableLogicalWidth = lineLogicalRight - lineLogicalLeft;
689}
690
691void LegacyLineLayout::computeInlineDirectionPositionsForLine(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox, const LineInfo& lineInfo, BidiRun* firstRun, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, bool reachedEnd, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache, WordMeasurements& wordMeasurements)
692{
693 TextAlignMode textAlign = textAlignmentForLine(!reachedEnd && !lineBox->endsWithBreak());
694
695 // CSS 2.1: "'Text-indent' only affects a line if it is the first formatted line of an element. For example, the first line of an anonymous block
696 // box is only affected if it is the first child of its parent element."
697 // CSS3 "text-indent", "-webkit-each-line" affects the first line of the block container as well as each line after a forced line break,
698 // but does not affect lines after a soft wrap break.
699 bool isFirstLine = lineInfo.isFirstLine() && !(m_flow.isAnonymousBlock() && m_flow.parent()->firstChild() != &m_flow);
700 bool isAfterHardLineBreak = lineBox->prevRootBox() && lineBox->prevRootBox()->endsWithBreak();
701 IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText = requiresIndent(isFirstLine, isAfterHardLineBreak, style());
702 float lineLogicalLeft;
703 float lineLogicalRight;
704 float availableLogicalWidth;
705 updateLogicalInlinePositions(m_flow, lineLogicalLeft, lineLogicalRight, availableLogicalWidth, isFirstLine, shouldIndentText, 0);
706 bool needsWordSpacing;
707
708 if (firstRun && firstRun->renderer().isReplaced()) {
709 RenderBox& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(firstRun->renderer());
710 updateLogicalInlinePositions(m_flow, lineLogicalLeft, lineLogicalRight, availableLogicalWidth, isFirstLine, shouldIndentText, renderBox.logicalHeight());
711 }
712
713 computeInlineDirectionPositionsForSegment(lineBox, lineInfo, textAlign, lineLogicalLeft, availableLogicalWidth, firstRun, trailingSpaceRun, textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache, wordMeasurements);
714 // The widths of all runs are now known. We can now place every inline box (and
715 // compute accurate widths for the inline flow boxes).
716 needsWordSpacing = false;
717 lineBox->placeBoxesInInlineDirection(lineLogicalLeft, needsWordSpacing);
718}
719
720static inline ExpansionBehavior expansionBehaviorForInlineTextBox(RenderBlockFlow& block, LegacyInlineTextBox& textBox, BidiRun* previousRun, BidiRun* nextRun, TextAlignMode textAlign, bool isAfterExpansion)
721{
722 // Tatechuyoko is modeled as the Object Replacement Character (U+FFFC), which can never have expansion opportunities inside nor intrinsically adjacent to it.
723 if (textBox.renderer().style().textCombine() == TextCombine::Horizontal)
724 return ForbidLeftExpansion | ForbidRightExpansion;
725
726 ExpansionBehavior result = 0;
727 bool setLeftExpansion = false;
728 bool setRightExpansion = false;
729 if (textAlign == TextAlignMode::Justify) {
730 // If the next box is ruby, and we're justifying, and the first box in the ruby base has a leading expansion, and we are a text box, then force a trailing expansion.
731 if (nextRun && is<RenderRubyRun>(nextRun->renderer()) && downcast<RenderRubyRun>(nextRun->renderer()).rubyBase() && nextRun->renderer().style().collapseWhiteSpace()) {
732 auto& rubyBase = *downcast<RenderRubyRun>(nextRun->renderer()).rubyBase();
733 if (rubyBase.firstRootBox() && !rubyBase.firstRootBox()->nextRootBox()) {
734 if (auto* leafChild = rubyBase.firstRootBox()->firstLeafDescendant()) {
735 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*leafChild)) {
736 // FIXME: This leftExpansionOpportunity doesn't actually work because it doesn't perform the UBA
737 if (FontCascade::leftExpansionOpportunity(downcast<RenderText>(leafChild->renderer()).stringView(), leafChild->direction())) {
738 setRightExpansion = true;
739 result |= ForceRightExpansion;
740 }
741 }
742 }
743 }
744 }
745 // Same thing, except if we're following a ruby
746 if (previousRun && is<RenderRubyRun>(previousRun->renderer()) && downcast<RenderRubyRun>(previousRun->renderer()).rubyBase() && previousRun->renderer().style().collapseWhiteSpace()) {
747 auto& rubyBase = *downcast<RenderRubyRun>(previousRun->renderer()).rubyBase();
748 if (rubyBase.firstRootBox() && !rubyBase.firstRootBox()->nextRootBox()) {
749 if (auto* leafChild = rubyBase.firstRootBox()->lastLeafDescendant()) {
750 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*leafChild)) {
751 // FIXME: This leftExpansionOpportunity doesn't actually work because it doesn't perform the UBA
752 if (FontCascade::rightExpansionOpportunity(downcast<RenderText>(leafChild->renderer()).stringView(), leafChild->direction())) {
753 setLeftExpansion = true;
754 result |= ForceLeftExpansion;
755 }
756 }
757 }
758 }
759 }
760 // If we're the first box inside a ruby base, forbid a leading expansion, and vice-versa
761 if (is<RenderRubyBase>(block)) {
762 RenderRubyBase& rubyBase = downcast<RenderRubyBase>(block);
763 if (&textBox == rubyBase.firstRootBox()->firstLeafDescendant()) {
764 setLeftExpansion = true;
765 result |= ForbidLeftExpansion;
766 } if (&textBox == rubyBase.firstRootBox()->lastLeafDescendant()) {
767 setRightExpansion = true;
768 result |= ForbidRightExpansion;
769 }
770 }
771 }
772 if (!setLeftExpansion)
773 result |= isAfterExpansion ? ForbidLeftExpansion : AllowLeftExpansion;
774 if (!setRightExpansion)
775 result |= AllowRightExpansion;
776 return result;
777}
778
779static inline void applyExpansionBehavior(LegacyInlineTextBox& textBox, ExpansionBehavior expansionBehavior)
780{
781 switch (expansionBehavior & LeftExpansionMask) {
782 case ForceLeftExpansion:
783 textBox.setForceLeftExpansion();
784 break;
785 case ForbidLeftExpansion:
786 textBox.setCanHaveLeftExpansion(false);
787 break;
788 case AllowLeftExpansion:
789 textBox.setCanHaveLeftExpansion(true);
790 break;
791 default:
792 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
793 break;
794 }
795 switch (expansionBehavior & RightExpansionMask) {
796 case ForceRightExpansion:
797 textBox.setForceRightExpansion();
798 break;
799 case ForbidRightExpansion:
800 textBox.setCanHaveRightExpansion(false);
801 break;
802 case AllowRightExpansion:
803 textBox.setCanHaveRightExpansion(true);
804 break;
805 default:
806 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
807 break;
808 }
809}
810
811static bool inlineAncestorHasStartBorderPaddingOrMargin(const RenderBlockFlow& block, const LegacyInlineBox& box)
812{
813 bool isLTR = block.style().isLeftToRightDirection();
814 for (auto* currentBox = box.parent(); currentBox; currentBox = currentBox->parent()) {
815 if ((isLTR && currentBox->marginBorderPaddingLogicalLeft() > 0)
816 || (!isLTR && currentBox->marginBorderPaddingLogicalRight() > 0))
817 return true;
818 }
819 return false;
820}
821
822static bool inlineAncestorHasEndBorderPaddingOrMargin(const RenderBlockFlow& block, const LegacyInlineBox& box)
823{
824 bool isLTR = block.style().isLeftToRightDirection();
825 for (auto* currentBox = box.parent(); currentBox; currentBox = currentBox->parent()) {
826 if ((isLTR && currentBox->marginBorderPaddingLogicalRight() > 0)
827 || (!isLTR && currentBox->marginBorderPaddingLogicalLeft() > 0))
828 return true;
829 }
830 return false;
831}
832
833static bool isLastInFlowRun(BidiRun& runToCheck)
834{
835 for (auto* run = runToCheck.next(); run; run = run->next()) {
836 if (!run->box() || run->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned() || run->box()->isLineBreak())
837 continue;
838 return false;
839 }
840 return true;
841}
842
843BidiRun* LegacyLineLayout::computeInlineDirectionPositionsForSegment(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox, const LineInfo& lineInfo, TextAlignMode textAlign, float& lineLogicalLeft,
844 float& availableLogicalWidth, BidiRun* firstRun, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache,
845 WordMeasurements& wordMeasurements)
846{
847 bool needsWordSpacing = false;
848 bool canHangPunctuationAtStart = style().hangingPunctuation().contains(HangingPunctuation::First);
849 bool canHangPunctuationAtEnd = style().hangingPunctuation().contains(HangingPunctuation::Last);
850 bool isLTR = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
851 float contentWidth = 0;
852 unsigned expansionOpportunityCount = 0;
853 bool isAfterExpansion = is<RenderRubyBase>(m_flow) ? downcast<RenderRubyBase>(m_flow).isAfterExpansion() : true;
854 Vector<unsigned, 16> expansionOpportunities;
855
856 HashMap<LegacyInlineTextBox*, LayoutUnit> logicalSpacingForInlineTextBoxes;
857 auto collectSpacingLogicalWidths = [&] () {
858 auto totalSpacingWidth = LayoutUnit { };
859 // Collect the spacing positions (margin, border padding) for the textboxes by traversing the inline tree of the current line.
860 Vector<LegacyInlineBox*> queue;
861 queue.append(lineBox);
862 // 1. Visit each inline box in a preorder fashion
863 // 2. Accumulate the spacing when we find an LegacyInlineFlowBox (inline container e.g. span)
864 // 3. Add the LegacyInlineTextBoxes to the hashmap
865 while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
866 while (true) {
867 auto* inlineBox = queue.last();
868 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(inlineBox)) {
869 auto& inlineFlowBox = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*inlineBox);
870 totalSpacingWidth += inlineFlowBox.marginBorderPaddingLogicalLeft();
871 if (auto* child = inlineFlowBox.firstChild()) {
872 queue.append(child);
873 continue;
874 }
875 break;
876 }
877 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(inlineBox))
878 logicalSpacingForInlineTextBoxes.add(downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(inlineBox), totalSpacingWidth);
879 break;
880 }
881 while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
882 auto& inlineBox = *queue.takeLast();
883 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(inlineBox))
884 totalSpacingWidth += downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(inlineBox).marginBorderPaddingLogicalRight();
885 if (auto* nextSibling = inlineBox.nextOnLine()) {
886 queue.append(nextSibling);
887 break;
888 }
889 }
890 }
891 };
892 collectSpacingLogicalWidths();
893
894 BidiRun* run = firstRun;
895 BidiRun* previousRun = nullptr;
896 for (; run; run = run->next()) {
897 auto computeExpansionOpportunities = [&expansionOpportunities, &expansionOpportunityCount, textAlign, &isAfterExpansion] (RenderBlockFlow& block,
898 LegacyInlineTextBox& textBox, BidiRun* previousRun, BidiRun* nextRun, const StringView& stringView, TextDirection direction)
899 {
900 if (stringView.isEmpty()) {
901 // Empty runs should still produce an entry in expansionOpportunities list so that the number of items matches the number of runs.
902 expansionOpportunities.append(0);
903 return;
904 }
905 ExpansionBehavior expansionBehavior = expansionBehaviorForInlineTextBox(block, textBox, previousRun, nextRun, textAlign, isAfterExpansion);
906 applyExpansionBehavior(textBox, expansionBehavior);
907 unsigned opportunitiesInRun;
908 std::tie(opportunitiesInRun, isAfterExpansion) = FontCascade::expansionOpportunityCount(stringView, direction, expansionBehavior);
909 expansionOpportunities.append(opportunitiesInRun);
910 expansionOpportunityCount += opportunitiesInRun;
911 };
912 if (!run->box() || run->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned() || run->box()->isLineBreak()) {
913 // Positioned objects are only participating to figure out their correct static x position.
914 // They have no effect on the width. Similarly, line break boxes have no effect on the width.
915 continue;
916 }
917 if (is<RenderText>(run->renderer())) {
918 auto& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(run->renderer());
919 auto& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*run->box());
920 if (canHangPunctuationAtStart && lineInfo.isFirstLine() && (isLTR || isLastInFlowRun(*run))
921 && !inlineAncestorHasStartBorderPaddingOrMargin(m_flow, *run->box())) {
922 float hangStartWidth = renderText.hangablePunctuationStartWidth(run->m_start);
923 availableLogicalWidth += hangStartWidth;
924 if (style().isLeftToRightDirection())
925 lineLogicalLeft -= hangStartWidth;
926 canHangPunctuationAtStart = false;
927 }
928
929 if (canHangPunctuationAtEnd && lineInfo.isLastLine() && run->m_stop > 0 && (!isLTR || isLastInFlowRun(*run))
930 && !inlineAncestorHasEndBorderPaddingOrMargin(m_flow, *run->box())) {
931 float hangEndWidth = renderText.hangablePunctuationEndWidth(run->m_stop - 1);
932 availableLogicalWidth += hangEndWidth;
933 if (!style().isLeftToRightDirection())
934 lineLogicalLeft -= hangEndWidth;
935 canHangPunctuationAtEnd = false;
936 }
937
938 if (textAlign == TextAlignMode::Justify && run != trailingSpaceRun)
939 computeExpansionOpportunities(m_flow, textBox, previousRun, run->next(), renderText.stringView(run->m_start, run->m_stop), run->box()->direction());
940
941 if (unsigned length = renderText.text().length()) {
942 if (!run->m_start && needsWordSpacing && isSpaceOrNewline(renderText.characterAt(run->m_start)))
943 contentWidth += lineStyle(*renderText.parent(), lineInfo).fontCascade().wordSpacing();
944 // run->m_start == run->m_stop should only be true iff the run is a replaced run for bidi: isolate.
945 ASSERT(run->m_stop > 0 || run->m_start == run->m_stop);
946 needsWordSpacing = run->m_stop == length && !isSpaceOrNewline(renderText.characterAt(run->m_stop - 1));
947 }
948 auto currentLogicalLeftPosition = logicalSpacingForInlineTextBoxes.get(&textBox) + contentWidth;
949 setLogicalWidthForTextRun(lineBox, run, renderText, currentLogicalLeftPosition, lineInfo, textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache, wordMeasurements);
950 } else {
951 canHangPunctuationAtStart = false;
952 bool encounteredJustifiedRuby = false;
953 if (is<RenderRubyRun>(run->renderer()) && textAlign == TextAlignMode::Justify && run != trailingSpaceRun && downcast<RenderRubyRun>(run->renderer()).rubyBase()) {
954 auto* rubyBase = downcast<RenderRubyRun>(run->renderer()).rubyBase();
955 if (rubyBase->firstRootBox() && !rubyBase->firstRootBox()->nextRootBox() && run->renderer().style().collapseWhiteSpace()) {
956 rubyBase->setIsAfterExpansion(isAfterExpansion);
957 for (auto* leafChild = rubyBase->firstRootBox()->firstLeafDescendant(); leafChild; leafChild = leafChild->nextLeafOnLine()) {
958 if (!is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*leafChild))
959 continue;
960 encounteredJustifiedRuby = true;
961 computeExpansionOpportunities(*rubyBase, downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*leafChild), nullptr, nullptr,
962 downcast<RenderText>(leafChild->renderer()).stringView(), leafChild->direction());
963 }
964 }
965 }
966
967 if (!encounteredJustifiedRuby)
968 isAfterExpansion = false;
969
970 if (!is<RenderInline>(run->renderer())) {
971 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(run->renderer());
972 if (is<RenderRubyRun>(renderBox))
973 setMarginsForRubyRun(run, downcast<RenderRubyRun>(renderBox), previousRun ? &previousRun->renderer() : nullptr, lineInfo);
974 run->box()->setLogicalWidth(m_flow.logicalWidthForChild(renderBox));
975 contentWidth += m_flow.marginStartForChild(renderBox) + m_flow.marginEndForChild(renderBox);
976 }
977 }
978
979 contentWidth += run->box()->logicalWidth();
980 previousRun = run;
981 }
982
983 if (isAfterExpansion && !expansionOpportunities.isEmpty()) {
984 // FIXME: see <webkit.org/b/139393#c11>
985 int lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex = expansionOpportunities.size() - 1;
986 while (lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex >= 0 && !expansionOpportunities.at(lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex))
987 --lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex;
988 if (lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex >= 0) {
989 ASSERT(expansionOpportunities.at(lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex));
990 expansionOpportunities.at(lastValidExpansionOpportunitiesIndex)--;
991 expansionOpportunityCount--;
992 }
993 }
994
995 if (is<RenderRubyBase>(m_flow) && !expansionOpportunityCount)
996 textAlign = TextAlignMode::Center;
997
998 auto totalLogicalWidth = contentWidth + lineBox->getFlowSpacingLogicalWidth();
999 updateLogicalWidthForAlignment(m_flow, textAlign, lineBox, trailingSpaceRun, lineLogicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, expansionOpportunityCount);
1000 computeExpansionForJustifiedText(firstRun, trailingSpaceRun, expansionOpportunities, expansionOpportunityCount, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth);
1001 return run;
1002}
1003
1004void LegacyLineLayout::removeInlineBox(BidiRun& run, const LegacyRootInlineBox& rootLineBox) const
1005{
1006 auto* inlineBox = run.box();
1007#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1008 auto* inlineParent = inlineBox->parent();
1009 while (inlineParent && inlineParent != &rootLineBox) {
1010 ASSERT(!inlineParent->isDirty());
1011 inlineParent = inlineParent->parent();
1012 }
1013 ASSERT(!rootLineBox.isDirty());
1014#endif
1015 auto* parent = inlineBox->parent();
1016 inlineBox->removeFromParent();
1017
1018 auto& renderer = run.renderer();
1019 if (is<RenderText>(renderer))
1020 downcast<RenderText>(renderer).removeTextBox(downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*inlineBox));
1021 delete inlineBox;
1022 run.setBox(nullptr);
1023 // removeFromParent() unnecessarily dirties the ancestor subtree.
1024 auto* ancestor = parent;
1025 while (ancestor) {
1026 ancestor->markDirty(false);
1027 if (ancestor == &rootLineBox)
1028 break;
1029 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
1030 }
1031}
1032
1033void LegacyLineLayout::computeBlockDirectionPositionsForLine(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox, BidiRun* firstRun, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache)
1034{
1035 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(lineBox->alignBoxesInBlockDirection(m_flow.logicalHeight(), textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache));
1036
1037 // Now make sure we place replaced render objects correctly.
1038 for (auto* run = firstRun; run; run = run->next()) {
1039 ASSERT(run->box());
1040 if (!run->box())
1041 continue; // Skip runs with no line boxes.
1042
1043 // Align positioned boxes with the top of the line box. This is
1044 // a reasonable approximation of an appropriate y position.
1045 auto& renderer = run->renderer();
1046 if (renderer.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
1047 run->box()->setLogicalTop(m_flow.logicalHeight());
1048
1049 // Position is used to properly position both replaced elements and
1050 // to update the static normal flow x/y of positioned elements.
1051 bool inlineBoxIsRedundant = false;
1052 if (is<RenderText>(renderer)) {
1053 auto& inlineTextBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*run->box());
1054 downcast<RenderText>(renderer).positionLineBox(inlineTextBox);
1055 inlineBoxIsRedundant = !inlineTextBox.hasTextContent();
1056 } else if (is<RenderBox>(renderer)) {
1057 downcast<RenderBox>(renderer).positionLineBox(downcast<LegacyInlineElementBox>(*run->box()));
1058 inlineBoxIsRedundant = renderer.isOutOfFlowPositioned();
1059 } else if (is<RenderLineBreak>(renderer))
1060 downcast<RenderLineBreak>(renderer).replaceInlineBoxWrapper(downcast<LegacyInlineElementBox>(*run->box()));
1061 // Check if we need to keep this box on the line at all.
1062 if (inlineBoxIsRedundant)
1063 removeInlineBox(*run, *lineBox);
1064 }
1065}
1066
1067static inline bool isCollapsibleSpace(UChar character, const RenderText& renderer)
1068{
1069 if (character == ' ' || character == '\t' || character == softHyphen)
1070 return true;
1071 if (character == '\n')
1072 return !renderer.style().preserveNewline();
1073 if (character == noBreakSpace)
1074 return renderer.style().nbspMode() == NBSPMode::Space;
1075 return false;
1076}
1077
1078template <typename CharacterType>
1079static inline unsigned findFirstTrailingSpace(const RenderText& lastText, const CharacterType* characters, unsigned start, unsigned stop)
1080{
1081 unsigned firstSpace = stop;
1082 while (firstSpace > start) {
1083 UChar current = characters[firstSpace - 1];
1084 if (!isCollapsibleSpace(current, lastText))
1085 break;
1086 firstSpace--;
1087 }
1088
1089 return firstSpace;
1090}
1091
1092inline BidiRun* LegacyLineLayout::handleTrailingSpaces(BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns, BidiContext* currentContext)
1093{
1094 if (!bidiRuns.runCount()
1095 || !bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->renderer().style().breakOnlyAfterWhiteSpace()
1096 || !bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->renderer().style().autoWrap())
1097 return nullptr;
1098
1099 BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun = bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun();
1100 const RenderObject& lastObject = trailingSpaceRun->renderer();
1101 if (!is<RenderText>(lastObject))
1102 return nullptr;
1103
1104 const RenderText& lastText = downcast<RenderText>(lastObject);
1105 unsigned firstSpace;
1106 if (lastText.text().is8Bit())
1107 firstSpace = findFirstTrailingSpace(lastText, lastText.text().characters8(), trailingSpaceRun->start(), trailingSpaceRun->stop());
1108 else
1109 firstSpace = findFirstTrailingSpace(lastText, lastText.text().characters16(), trailingSpaceRun->start(), trailingSpaceRun->stop());
1110
1111 if (firstSpace == trailingSpaceRun->stop())
1112 return nullptr;
1113
1114 TextDirection direction = style().direction();
1115 bool shouldReorder = trailingSpaceRun != (direction == TextDirection::LTR ? bidiRuns.lastRun() : bidiRuns.firstRun());
1116 if (firstSpace != trailingSpaceRun->start()) {
1117 BidiContext* baseContext = currentContext;
1118 while (BidiContext* parent = baseContext->parent())
1119 baseContext = parent;
1120
1121 std::unique_ptr<BidiRun> newTrailingRun = makeUnique<BidiRun>(firstSpace, trailingSpaceRun->m_stop, trailingSpaceRun->renderer(), baseContext, U_OTHER_NEUTRAL);
1122 trailingSpaceRun->m_stop = firstSpace;
1123 trailingSpaceRun = newTrailingRun.get();
1124 if (direction == TextDirection::LTR)
1125 bidiRuns.appendRun(WTFMove(newTrailingRun));
1126 else
1127 bidiRuns.prependRun(WTFMove(newTrailingRun));
1128 return trailingSpaceRun;
1129 }
1130 if (!shouldReorder)
1131 return trailingSpaceRun;
1132
1133 if (direction == TextDirection::LTR) {
1134 bidiRuns.moveRunToEnd(trailingSpaceRun);
1135 trailingSpaceRun->m_level = 0;
1136 } else {
1137 bidiRuns.moveRunToBeginning(trailingSpaceRun);
1138 trailingSpaceRun->m_level = 1;
1139 }
1140 return trailingSpaceRun;
1141}
1142
1143void LegacyLineLayout::appendFloatingObjectToLastLine(FloatingObject& floatingObject)
1144{
1145 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!floatingObject.originatingLine());
1146 ASSERT(lastRootBox());
1147 floatingObject.setOriginatingLine(*lastRootBox());
1148 lastRootBox()->appendFloat(floatingObject.renderer());
1149}
