1151static inline void notifyResolverToResumeInIsolate(InlineBidiResolver& resolver, RenderObject* root, RenderObject* startObject)
1152{
1153 if (root != startObject) {
1154 RenderObject* parent = startObject->parent();
1155 notifyResolverToResumeInIsolate(resolver, root, parent);
1156 notifyObserverEnteredObject(&resolver, startObject);
1157 }
1158}
1159
1160static inline void setUpResolverToResumeInIsolate(InlineBidiResolver& resolver, InlineBidiResolver& topResolver, BidiRun& isolatedRun, RenderObject* root, RenderObject* startObject)
1161{
1162 // Set up m_whitespaceCollapsingState
1163 resolver.whitespaceCollapsingState() = topResolver.whitespaceCollapsingState();
1164 resolver.whitespaceCollapsingState().setCurrentTransition(topResolver.whitespaceCollapsingTransitionForIsolatedRun(isolatedRun));
1165
1166 // Set up m_nestedIsolateCount
1167 notifyResolverToResumeInIsolate(resolver, root, startObject);
1168}
1169
1170// FIXME: BidiResolver should have this logic.
1171static inline void constructBidiRunsForSegment(InlineBidiResolver& topResolver, BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns, const InlineIterator& endOfRuns, VisualDirectionOverride override, bool previousLineBrokeCleanly)
1172{
1173 // FIXME: We should pass a BidiRunList into createBidiRunsForLine instead
1174 // of the resolver owning the runs.
1175 ASSERT(&topResolver.runs() == &bidiRuns);
1176 ASSERT(topResolver.position() != endOfRuns);
1177 RenderObject* currentRoot = topResolver.position().root();
1178 topResolver.createBidiRunsForLine(endOfRuns, override, previousLineBrokeCleanly);
1179
1180 while (!topResolver.isolatedRuns().isEmpty()) {
1181 // It does not matter which order we resolve the runs as long as we resolve them all.
1182 auto isolatedRun = WTFMove(topResolver.isolatedRuns().last());
1183 topResolver.isolatedRuns().removeLast();
1184 currentRoot = &isolatedRun.root;
1185
1186 RenderObject& startObject = isolatedRun.object;
1187
1188 // Only inlines make sense with unicode-bidi: isolate (blocks are already isolated).
1189 // FIXME: Because enterIsolate is not passed a RenderObject, we have to crawl up the
1190 // tree to see which parent inline is the isolate. We could change enterIsolate
1191 // to take a RenderObject and do this logic there, but that would be a layering
1192 // violation for BidiResolver (which knows nothing about RenderObject).
1193 RenderInline* isolatedInline = downcast<RenderInline>(highestContainingIsolateWithinRoot(startObject, currentRoot));
1194 ASSERT(isolatedInline);
1195
1196 InlineBidiResolver isolatedResolver;
1197 EUnicodeBidi unicodeBidi = isolatedInline->style().unicodeBidi();
1198 TextDirection direction;
1199 if (unicodeBidi == Plaintext)
1200 determineDirectionality(direction, InlineIterator(isolatedInline, &isolatedRun.object, 0));
1201 else {
1202 ASSERT(unicodeBidi == Isolate || unicodeBidi == IsolateOverride);
1203 direction = isolatedInline->style().direction();
1204 }
1205 isolatedResolver.setStatus(BidiStatus(direction, isOverride(unicodeBidi)));
1206
1207 setUpResolverToResumeInIsolate(isolatedResolver, topResolver, isolatedRun.runToReplace, isolatedInline, &startObject);
1208
1209 // The starting position is the beginning of the first run within the isolate that was identified
1210 // during the earlier call to createBidiRunsForLine. This can be but is not necessarily the
1211 // first run within the isolate.
1212 InlineIterator iter = InlineIterator(isolatedInline, &startObject, isolatedRun.position);
1213 isolatedResolver.setPositionIgnoringNestedIsolates(iter);
1214
1215 // We stop at the next end of line; we may re-enter this isolate in the next call to constructBidiRuns().
1216 // FIXME: What should end and previousLineBrokeCleanly be?
1217 // rniwa says previousLineBrokeCleanly is just a WinIE hack and could always be false here?
1218 isolatedResolver.createBidiRunsForLine(endOfRuns, NoVisualOverride, previousLineBrokeCleanly);
1219 // Note that we do not delete the runs from the resolver.
1220 // We're not guaranteed to get any BidiRuns in the previous step. If we don't, we allow the placeholder
1221 // itself to be turned into an InlineBox. We can't remove it here without potentially losing track of
1222 // the logically last run.
1223 if (isolatedResolver.runs().runCount())
1224 bidiRuns.replaceRunWithRuns(&isolatedRun.runToReplace, isolatedResolver.runs());
1225
1226 // If we encountered any nested isolate runs, just move them
1227 // to the top resolver's list for later processing.
1228 while (!isolatedResolver.isolatedRuns().isEmpty()) {
1229 auto runWithContext = WTFMove(isolatedResolver.isolatedRuns().last());
1230 isolatedResolver.isolatedRuns().removeLast();
1231 topResolver.setWhitespaceCollapsingTransitionForIsolatedRun(runWithContext.runToReplace, isolatedResolver.whitespaceCollapsingTransitionForIsolatedRun(runWithContext.runToReplace));
1232 topResolver.isolatedRuns().append(WTFMove(runWithContext));
1233 }
1234 }
1235}
1236
1237// This function constructs line boxes for all of the text runs in the resolver and computes their position.
1238LegacyRootInlineBox* LegacyLineLayout::createLineBoxesFromBidiRuns(unsigned bidiLevel, BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns, const InlineIterator& end, LineInfo& lineInfo, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache, BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun, WordMeasurements& wordMeasurements)
1239{
1240 if (!bidiRuns.runCount())
1241 return nullptr;
1242
1243 // FIXME: Why is this only done when we had runs?
1244 lineInfo.setLastLine(!end.renderer());
1245
1246 LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox = constructLine(bidiRuns, lineInfo);
1247 if (!lineBox)
1248 return nullptr;
1249
1250 lineBox->setBidiLevel(bidiLevel);
1251 lineBox->setEndsWithBreak(lineInfo.previousLineBrokeCleanly());
1252
1253 bool isSVGRootInlineBox = is<SVGRootInlineBox>(*lineBox);
1254
1255 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap textBoxDataMap;
1256
1257 // Now we position all of our text runs horizontally.
1258 if (!isSVGRootInlineBox)
1259 computeInlineDirectionPositionsForLine(lineBox, lineInfo, bidiRuns.firstRun(), trailingSpaceRun, end.atEnd(), textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache, wordMeasurements);
1260
1261 // Now position our text runs vertically.
1262 computeBlockDirectionPositionsForLine(lineBox, bidiRuns.firstRun(), textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache);
1263
1264 // SVG text layout code computes vertical & horizontal positions on its own.
1265 // Note that we still need to execute computeVerticalPositionsForLine() as
1266 // it calls LegacyInlineTextBox::positionLineBox(), which tracks whether the box
1267 // contains reversed text or not. If we wouldn't do that editing and thus
1268 // text selection in RTL boxes would not work as expected.
1269 if (isSVGRootInlineBox) {
1270 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(m_flow.isSVGText());
1271 downcast<SVGRootInlineBox>(*lineBox).computePerCharacterLayoutInformation();
1272 }
1273
1274 // Compute our overflow now.
1275 lineBox->computeOverflow(lineBox->lineTop(), lineBox->lineBottom(), textBoxDataMap);
1276
1277 return lineBox;
1278}
1279
1280static void deleteLineRange(LineLayoutState& layoutState, LegacyRootInlineBox* startLine, LegacyRootInlineBox* stopLine = 0)
1281{
1282 LegacyRootInlineBox* boxToDelete = startLine;
1283 while (boxToDelete && boxToDelete != stopLine) {
1284 layoutState.updateRepaintRangeFromBox(boxToDelete);
1285 // Note: deleteLineRange(firstRootBox()) is not identical to deleteLineBoxTree().
1286 // deleteLineBoxTree uses nextLineBox() instead of nextRootBox() when traversing.
1287 LegacyRootInlineBox* next = boxToDelete->nextRootBox();
1288 boxToDelete->deleteLine();
1289 boxToDelete = next;
1290 }
1291}
1292
1293static void repaintDirtyFloats(LineLayoutState::FloatList& floats)
1294{
1295 // Floats that did not have layout did not repaint when we laid them out. They would have
1296 // painted by now if they had moved, but if they stayed at (0, 0), they still need to be
1297 // painted.
1298 for (auto& floatBox : floats) {
1299 if (floatBox->everHadLayout())
1300 continue;
1301 auto& box = floatBox->renderer();
1302 if (!box.x() && !box.y() && box.checkForRepaintDuringLayout())
1303 box.repaint();
1304 }
1305}
1306
1307void LegacyLineLayout::layoutRunsAndFloats(LineLayoutState& layoutState, bool hasInlineChild)
1308{
1309 // We want to skip ahead to the first dirty line
1310 InlineBidiResolver resolver;
1311 LegacyRootInlineBox* startLine = determineStartPosition(layoutState, resolver);
1312
1313 unsigned consecutiveHyphenatedLines = 0;
1314 if (startLine) {
1315 for (auto* line = startLine->prevRootBox(); line && line->isHyphenated(); line = line->prevRootBox())
1316 consecutiveHyphenatedLines++;
1317 }
1318
1319 // FIXME: This would make more sense outside of this function, but since
1320 // determineStartPosition can change the fullLayout flag we have to do this here. Failure to call
1321 // determineStartPosition first will break fast/repaint/line-flow-with-floats-9.html.
1322 if (layoutState.isFullLayout() && hasInlineChild && !m_flow.selfNeedsLayout()) {
1323 m_flow.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis); // Mark as needing a full layout to force us to repaint.
1324 if (!layoutContext().needsFullRepaint() && m_flow.layerRepaintRects()) {
1325 // Because we waited until we were already inside layout to discover
1326 // that the block really needed a full layout, we missed our chance to repaint the layer
1327 // before layout started. Luckily the layer has cached the repaint rect for its original
1328 // position and size, and so we can use that to make a repaint happen now.
1329 m_flow.repaintUsingContainer(m_flow.containerForRepaint(), m_flow.layerRepaintRects()->clippedOverflowRect);
1330 }
1331 }
1332
1333 if (m_flow.containsFloats())
1334 layoutState.floatList().setLastFloat(m_flow.floatingObjects()->set().last().get());
1335
1336 // We also find the first clean line and extract these lines. We will add them back
1337 // if we determine that we're able to synchronize after handling all our dirty lines.
1338 InlineIterator cleanLineStart;
1339 BidiStatus cleanLineBidiStatus;
1340 if (!layoutState.isFullLayout() && startLine)
1341 determineEndPosition(layoutState, startLine, cleanLineStart, cleanLineBidiStatus);
1342
1343 if (startLine) {
1344 if (!layoutState.usesRepaintBounds())
1345 layoutState.setRepaintRange(m_flow.logicalHeight());
1346 deleteLineRange(layoutState, startLine);
1347 }
1348
1349 if (!layoutState.isFullLayout() && lastRootBox() && lastRootBox()->endsWithBreak()) {
1350 // If the last line before the start line ends with a line break that clear floats,
1351 // adjust the height accordingly.
1352 // A line break can be either the first or the last object on a line, depending on its direction.
1353 if (LegacyInlineBox* lastLeafDescendant = lastRootBox()->lastLeafDescendant()) {
1354 RenderObject* lastObject = &lastLeafDescendant->renderer();
1355 if (!lastObject->isBR())
1356 lastObject = &lastRootBox()->firstLeafDescendant()->renderer();
1357 if (lastObject->isBR()) {
1358 auto clear = RenderStyle::usedClear(*lastObject);
1359 if (clear != UsedClear::None)
1360 m_flow.clearFloats(clear);
1361 }
1362 }
1363 }
1364
1365 layoutRunsAndFloatsInRange(layoutState, resolver, cleanLineStart, cleanLineBidiStatus, consecutiveHyphenatedLines);
1366 linkToEndLineIfNeeded(layoutState);
1367 repaintDirtyFloats(layoutState.floatList());
1368}
1369
1370// Before restarting the layout loop with a new logicalHeight, remove all floats that were added and reset the resolver.
1371inline const InlineIterator& LegacyLineLayout::restartLayoutRunsAndFloatsInRange(LayoutUnit oldLogicalHeight, LayoutUnit newLogicalHeight, FloatingObject* lastFloatFromPreviousLine, InlineBidiResolver& resolver, const InlineIterator& oldEnd)
1372{
1373 m_flow.removeFloatingObjectsBelow(lastFloatFromPreviousLine, oldLogicalHeight);
1374 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(newLogicalHeight);
1375 resolver.setPositionIgnoringNestedIsolates(oldEnd);
1376 return oldEnd;
1377}
1378
1379void LegacyLineLayout::layoutRunsAndFloatsInRange(LineLayoutState& layoutState, InlineBidiResolver& resolver, const InlineIterator& cleanLineStart, const BidiStatus& cleanLineBidiStatus, unsigned consecutiveHyphenatedLines)
1380{
1381 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
1382 bool paginated = layoutContext().layoutState() && layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated();
1383 LineWhitespaceCollapsingState& lineWhitespaceCollapsingState = resolver.whitespaceCollapsingState();
1384 InlineIterator end = resolver.position();
1385 bool checkForEndLineMatch = layoutState.endLine();
1386 RenderTextInfo renderTextInfo;
1387 VerticalPositionCache verticalPositionCache;
1388
1389 LineBreaker lineBreaker(m_flow);
1390
1391 while (!end.atEnd()) {
1392 // FIXME: Is this check necessary before the first iteration or can it be moved to the end?
1393 if (checkForEndLineMatch) {
1394 layoutState.setEndLineMatched(matchedEndLine(layoutState, resolver, cleanLineStart, cleanLineBidiStatus));
1395 if (layoutState.endLineMatched()) {
1396 resolver.setPosition(InlineIterator(resolver.position().root(), 0, 0), 0);
1397 layoutState.marginInfo().clearMargin();
1398 break;
1399 }
1400 }
1401
1402 lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.reset();
1403
1404 layoutState.lineInfo().setEmpty(true);
1405 layoutState.lineInfo().resetRunsFromLeadingWhitespace();
1406
1407 const InlineIterator oldEnd = end;
1408 bool isNewUBAParagraph = layoutState.lineInfo().previousLineBrokeCleanly();
1409 FloatingObject* lastFloatFromPreviousLine = (m_flow.containsFloats()) ? m_flow.floatingObjects()->set().last().get() : nullptr;
1410
1411 WordMeasurements wordMeasurements;
1412 end = lineBreaker.nextLineBreak(resolver, layoutState.lineInfo(), renderTextInfo, lastFloatFromPreviousLine, consecutiveHyphenatedLines, wordMeasurements);
1413 m_flow.cachePriorCharactersIfNeeded(renderTextInfo.lineBreakIterator);
1414 renderTextInfo.lineBreakIterator.resetPriorContext();
1415 if (resolver.position().atEnd()) {
1416 // FIXME: We shouldn't be creating any runs in nextLineBreak to begin with!
1417 // Once BidiRunList is separated from BidiResolver this will not be needed.
1418 resolver.runs().clear();
1419 resolver.markCurrentRunEmpty(); // FIXME: This can probably be replaced by an ASSERT (or just removed).
1420 layoutState.setCheckForFloatsFromLastLine(true);
1421 resolver.setPosition(InlineIterator(resolver.position().root(), 0, 0), 0);
1422 break;
1423 }
1424
1425 ASSERT(end != resolver.position());
1426
1427 // This is a short-cut for empty lines.
1428 if (layoutState.lineInfo().isEmpty()) {
1429 if (lastRootBox())
1430 lastRootBox()->setLineBreakInfo(end.renderer(), end.offset(), resolver.status());
1431 } else {
1432 VisualDirectionOverride override = (styleToUse.rtlOrdering() == Order::Visual ? (styleToUse.direction() == TextDirection::LTR ? VisualLeftToRightOverride : VisualRightToLeftOverride) : NoVisualOverride);
1433
1434 if (isNewUBAParagraph && styleToUse.unicodeBidi() == Plaintext && !resolver.context()->parent()) {
1435 TextDirection direction = styleToUse.direction();
1436 determineDirectionality(direction, resolver.position());
1437 resolver.setStatus(BidiStatus(direction, isOverride(styleToUse.unicodeBidi())));
1438 }
1439 // FIXME: This ownership is reversed. We should own the BidiRunList and pass it to createBidiRunsForLine.
1440 BidiRunList<BidiRun>& bidiRuns = resolver.runs();
1441 constructBidiRunsForSegment(resolver, bidiRuns, end, override, layoutState.lineInfo().previousLineBrokeCleanly());
1442 ASSERT(resolver.position() == end);
1443
1444 BidiRun* trailingSpaceRun = !layoutState.lineInfo().previousLineBrokeCleanly() ? handleTrailingSpaces(bidiRuns, resolver.context()) : nullptr;
1445
1446 if (bidiRuns.runCount() && lineBreaker.lineWasHyphenated()) {
1447 bidiRuns.logicallyLastRun()->m_hasHyphen = true;
1448 consecutiveHyphenatedLines++;
1449 } else
1450 consecutiveHyphenatedLines = 0;
1451
1452 // Now that the runs have been ordered, we create the line boxes.
1453 // At the same time we figure out where border/padding/margin should be applied for
1454 // inline flow boxes.
1455
1456 LayoutUnit oldLogicalHeight = m_flow.logicalHeight();
1457 LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox = createLineBoxesFromBidiRuns(resolver.status().context->level(), bidiRuns, end, layoutState.lineInfo(), verticalPositionCache, trailingSpaceRun, wordMeasurements);
1458
1459 bidiRuns.clear();
1460 resolver.markCurrentRunEmpty(); // FIXME: This can probably be replaced by an ASSERT (or just removed).
1461
1462 if (lineBox) {
1463 lineBox->setLineBreakInfo(end.renderer(), end.offset(), resolver.status());
1464 if (layoutState.usesRepaintBounds())
1465 layoutState.updateRepaintRangeFromBox(lineBox);
1466
1467 LayoutUnit adjustment;
1468 bool overflowsFragment = false;
1469
1470 layoutState.marginInfo().setAtBeforeSideOfBlock(false);
1471
1472 if (paginated)
1473 m_flow.adjustLinePositionForPagination(lineBox, adjustment, overflowsFragment, layoutState.fragmentedFlow());
1474 if (adjustment) {
1475 IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText = layoutState.lineInfo().isFirstLine() ? IndentText : DoNotIndentText;
1476 LayoutUnit oldLineWidth = m_flow.availableLogicalWidthForLine(oldLogicalHeight, shouldIndentText);
1477 lineBox->adjustBlockDirectionPosition(adjustment);
1478 if (layoutState.usesRepaintBounds())
1479 layoutState.updateRepaintRangeFromBox(lineBox);
1480
1481 if (m_flow.availableLogicalWidthForLine(oldLogicalHeight + adjustment, shouldIndentText) != oldLineWidth) {
1482 // We have to delete this line, remove all floats that got added, and let line layout re-run.
1483 lineBox->deleteLine();
1484 end = restartLayoutRunsAndFloatsInRange(oldLogicalHeight, oldLogicalHeight + adjustment, lastFloatFromPreviousLine, resolver, oldEnd);
1485 continue;
1486 }
1487
1488 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(lineBox->lineBoxBottom());
1489 }
1490
1491 if (paginated) {
1492 if (layoutState.fragmentedFlow())
1493 updateFragmentForLine(lineBox);
1494 }
1495 }
1496 }
1497
1498 for (size_t i = 0; i < lineBreaker.positionedObjects().size(); ++i)
1499 setStaticPositions(m_flow, *lineBreaker.positionedObjects()[i], DoNotIndentText);
1500
1501 if (!layoutState.lineInfo().isEmpty()) {
1502 layoutState.lineInfo().setFirstLine(false);
1503 m_flow.clearFloats(lineBreaker.usedClear());
1504 }
1505
1506 if (m_flow.floatingObjects() && lastRootBox()) {
1507 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_flow.floatingObjects()->set();
1508 auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin();
1509 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
1510 if (auto* lastFloat = layoutState.floatList().lastFloat()) {
1511 auto lastFloatIterator = floatingObjectSet.find(lastFloat);
1512 ASSERT(lastFloatIterator != end);
1513 ++lastFloatIterator;
1514 it = lastFloatIterator;
1515 }
1516 for (; it != end; ++it) {
1517 auto& floatingObject = *it;
1518 appendFloatingObjectToLastLine(*floatingObject);
1519 // If a float's geometry has changed, give up on syncing with clean lines.
1520 auto* floatWithRect = layoutState.floatList().floatWithRect(floatingObject->renderer());
1521 if (!floatWithRect || floatWithRect->rect() != floatingObject->frameRect())
1522 checkForEndLineMatch = false;
1523 }
1524 layoutState.floatList().setLastFloat(!floatingObjectSet.isEmpty() ? floatingObjectSet.last().get() : nullptr);
1525 }
1526
1527 lineWhitespaceCollapsingState.reset();
1528 resolver.setPosition(end, numberOfIsolateAncestors(end));
1529 }
1530
1531 // In case we already adjusted the line positions during this layout to avoid widows
1532 // then we need to ignore the possibility of having a new widows situation.
1533 // Otherwise, we risk leaving empty containers which is against the block fragmentation principles.
1534 if (paginated && !style().hasAutoWidows() && !m_flow.didBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow()) {
1535 // Check the line boxes to make sure we didn't create unacceptable widows.
1536 // However, we'll prioritize orphans - so nothing we do here should create
1537 // a new orphan.
1538
1539 LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox = lastRootBox();
1540
1541 // Count from the end of the block backwards, to see how many hanging
1542 // lines we have.
1543 LegacyRootInlineBox* firstLineInBlock = firstRootBox();
1544 int numLinesHanging = 1;
1545 while (lineBox && lineBox != firstLineInBlock && !lineBox->isFirstAfterPageBreak()) {
1546 ++numLinesHanging;
1547 lineBox = lineBox->prevRootBox();
1548 }
1549
1550 // If there were no breaks in the block, we didn't create any widows.
1551 if (!lineBox || !lineBox->isFirstAfterPageBreak() || lineBox == firstLineInBlock) {
1552 if (m_flow.shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow()) {
1553 // This is the case when the previous line layout marks a line to break at to avoid widows
1554 // but the current layout does not produce that line. It happens when layout constraints unexpectedly
1555 // change in between layouts (note that these paginated line layouts run within the same layout frame
1556 // as opposed to two subsequent full layouts).
1557 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1558 m_flow.clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow();
1559 }
1560 return;
1561 }
1562
1563 if (numLinesHanging < style().widows()) {
1564 // We have detected a widow. Now we need to work out how many
1565 // lines there are on the previous page, and how many we need
1566 // to steal.
1567 int numLinesNeeded = style().widows() - numLinesHanging;
1568 LegacyRootInlineBox* currentFirstLineOfNewPage = lineBox;
1569
1570 // Count the number of lines in the previous page.
1571 lineBox = lineBox->prevRootBox();
1572 int numLinesInPreviousPage = 1;
1573 while (lineBox && lineBox != firstLineInBlock && !lineBox->isFirstAfterPageBreak()) {
1574 ++numLinesInPreviousPage;
1575 lineBox = lineBox->prevRootBox();
1576 }
1577
1578 // If there was an explicit value for orphans, respect that. If not, we still
1579 // shouldn't create a situation where we make an orphan bigger than the initial value.
1580 // This means that setting widows implies we also care about orphans, but given
1581 // the specification says the initial orphan value is non-zero, this is ok. The
1582 // author is always free to set orphans explicitly as well.
1583 int orphans = style().hasAutoOrphans() ? style().initialOrphans() : style().orphans();
1584 int numLinesAvailable = numLinesInPreviousPage - orphans;
1585 if (numLinesAvailable <= 0)
1586 return;
1587
1588 int numLinesToTake = std::min(numLinesAvailable, numLinesNeeded);
1589 // Wind back from our first widowed line.
1590 lineBox = currentFirstLineOfNewPage;
1591 for (int i = 0; i < numLinesToTake; ++i)
1592 lineBox = lineBox->prevRootBox();
1593
1594 // We now want to break at this line. Remember for next layout and trigger relayout.
1595 m_flow.setBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow(lineCountUntil(lineBox));
1596 m_flow.markLinesDirtyInBlockRange(lastRootBox()->lineBoxBottom(), lineBox->lineBoxBottom(), lineBox);
1597 }
1598 }
1599 m_flow.clearDidBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow();
1600}
1601
1602void LegacyLineLayout::reattachCleanLineFloats(LegacyRootInlineBox& cleanLine, LayoutUnit delta, bool isFirstCleanLine)
1603{
1604 auto* cleanLineFloats = cleanLine.floatsPtr();
1605 if (!cleanLineFloats)
1606 return;
1607
1608 for (auto& floatingBox : *cleanLineFloats) {
1609 if (!floatingBox)
1610 continue;
1611 auto* floatingObject = m_flow.insertFloatingObject(*floatingBox);
1612 if (isFirstCleanLine && floatingObject->originatingLine()) {
1613 // Float box does not belong to this line anymore.
1614 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(cleanLine.prevRootBox() == floatingObject->originatingLine());
1615 cleanLine.removeFloat(*floatingBox);
1616 continue;
1617 }
1618 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!floatingObject->originatingLine());
1619 floatingObject->setOriginatingLine(cleanLine);
1620 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(m_flow.logicalTopForChild(*floatingBox) - m_flow.marginBeforeForChild(*floatingBox) + delta);
1621 m_flow.positionNewFloats();
1622 }
1623}
1624
1625void LegacyLineLayout::linkToEndLineIfNeeded(LineLayoutState& layoutState)
1626{
1627 auto* firstCleanLine = layoutState.endLine();
1628 if (firstCleanLine) {
1629 if (layoutState.endLineMatched()) {
1630 bool paginated = layoutContext().layoutState() && layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated();
1631 // Attach all the remaining lines, and then adjust their y-positions as needed.
1632 LayoutUnit delta = m_flow.logicalHeight() - layoutState.endLineLogicalTop();
1633 for (auto* line = firstCleanLine; line; line = line->nextRootBox()) {
1634 line->attachLine();
1635 if (paginated) {
1636 delta -= line->paginationStrut();
1637 bool overflowsFragment;
1638 m_flow.adjustLinePositionForPagination(line, delta, overflowsFragment, layoutState.fragmentedFlow());
1639 }
1640 if (delta) {
1641 layoutState.updateRepaintRangeFromBox(line, delta);
1642 line->adjustBlockDirectionPosition(delta);
1643 }
1644 if (layoutState.fragmentedFlow())
1645 updateFragmentForLine(line);
1646 reattachCleanLineFloats(*line, delta, line == firstCleanLine);
1647 }
1648 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(lastRootBox()->lineBoxBottom());
1649 } else {
1650 // Delete all the remaining lines.
1651 deleteLineRange(layoutState, layoutState.endLine());
1652 }
1653 }
1654
1655 if (m_flow.floatingObjects() && (layoutState.checkForFloatsFromLastLine() || m_flow.positionNewFloats()) && lastRootBox()) {
1656 // In case we have a float on the last line, it might not be positioned up to now.
1657 // This has to be done before adding in the bottom border/padding, or the float will
1658 // include the padding incorrectly. -dwh
1659 if (layoutState.checkForFloatsFromLastLine()) {
1660 LayoutUnit bottomVisualOverflow = lastRootBox()->logicalBottomVisualOverflow();
1661 LayoutUnit bottomLayoutOverflow = lastRootBox()->logicalBottomLayoutOverflow();
1662 auto newLineBox = makeUnique<LegacyRootInlineBox>(m_flow);
1663 newLineBox->setIsForTrailingFloats();
1664 auto trailingFloatsLineBox = newLineBox.get();
1665 m_lineBoxes.appendLineBox(WTFMove(newLineBox));
1666 trailingFloatsLineBox->setConstructed();
1667 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap textBoxDataMap;
1668 VerticalPositionCache verticalPositionCache;
1669 LayoutUnit blockLogicalHeight = m_flow.logicalHeight();
1670 trailingFloatsLineBox->alignBoxesInBlockDirection(blockLogicalHeight, textBoxDataMap, verticalPositionCache);
1671 trailingFloatsLineBox->setLineTopBottomPositions(blockLogicalHeight, blockLogicalHeight, blockLogicalHeight, blockLogicalHeight);
1672 trailingFloatsLineBox->setPaginatedLineWidth(m_flow.availableLogicalWidthForContent(blockLogicalHeight));
1673 LayoutRect logicalLayoutOverflow(0_lu, blockLogicalHeight, 1_lu, bottomLayoutOverflow - blockLogicalHeight);
1674 LayoutRect logicalVisualOverflow(0_lu, blockLogicalHeight, 1_lu, bottomVisualOverflow - blockLogicalHeight);
1675 trailingFloatsLineBox->setOverflowFromLogicalRects(logicalLayoutOverflow, logicalVisualOverflow, trailingFloatsLineBox->lineTop(), trailingFloatsLineBox->lineBottom());
1676 if (layoutState.fragmentedFlow())
1677 updateFragmentForLine(trailingFloatsLineBox);
1678 }
1679
1680 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_flow.floatingObjects()->set();
1681 auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin();
1682 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
1683 if (auto* lastFloat = layoutState.floatList().lastFloat()) {
1684 auto lastFloatIterator = floatingObjectSet.find(lastFloat);
1685 ASSERT(lastFloatIterator != end);
1686 ++lastFloatIterator;
1687 it = lastFloatIterator;
1688 }
1689 for (; it != end; ++it)
1690 appendFloatingObjectToLastLine(**it);
1691 layoutState.floatList().setLastFloat(!floatingObjectSet.isEmpty() ? floatingObjectSet.last().get() : nullptr);
1692 }
1693}
1694
1695void LegacyLineLayout::layoutLineBoxes(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalBottom)
1696{
1697 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(m_flow.borderAndPaddingBefore());
1698
1699 // Lay out our hypothetical grid line as though it occurs at the top of the block.
1700 if (layoutContext().layoutState() && layoutContext().layoutState()->lineGrid() == &m_flow)
1701 m_flow.layoutLineGridBox();
1702
1703 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = m_flow.enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1704 bool clearLinesForPagination = firstRootBox() && fragmentedFlow && !fragmentedFlow->hasFragments();
1705
1706 // Figure out if we should clear out our line boxes.
1707 // FIXME: Handle resize eventually!
1708 bool isFullLayout = !firstRootBox() || m_flow.selfNeedsLayout() || relayoutChildren || clearLinesForPagination;
1709 LineLayoutState layoutState(m_flow, isFullLayout, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom, fragmentedFlow);
1710
1711 if (isFullLayout)
1712 lineBoxes().deleteLineBoxes();
1713
1714 // Text truncation kicks in in two cases:
1715 // 1) If your overflow isn't visible and your text-overflow-mode isn't clip.
1716 // 2) If you're an anonymous block with a block parent that satisfies #1.
1717 // FIXME: CSS3 says that descendants that are clipped must also know how to truncate. This is insanely
1718 // difficult to figure out in general (especially in the middle of doing layout), so we only handle the
1719 // simple case of an anonymous block truncating when it's parent is clipped.
1720 auto* parent = m_flow.parent();
1721 bool hasTextOverflow = (style().textOverflow() == TextOverflow::Ellipsis && m_flow.hasOverflowClip())
1722 || (m_flow.isAnonymousBlock() && parent && parent->isRenderBlock() && parent->style().textOverflow() == TextOverflow::Ellipsis && parent->hasOverflowClip());
1723
1724 // Walk all the lines and delete our ellipsis line boxes if they exist.
1725 if (hasTextOverflow)
1726 deleteEllipsisLineBoxes();
1727
1728 if (m_flow.firstChild()) {
1729 // In full layout mode, clear the line boxes of children upfront. Otherwise,
1730 // siblings can run into stale root lineboxes during layout. Then layout
1731 // the replaced elements later. In partial layout mode, line boxes are not
1732 // deleted and only dirtied. In that case, we can layout the replaced
1733 // elements at the same time.
1734 bool hasInlineChild = false;
1735 Vector<RenderBox*> replacedChildren;
1736 for (InlineWalker walker(m_flow); !walker.atEnd(); walker.advance()) {
1737 RenderObject& o = *walker.current();
1738
1739 if (!hasInlineChild && o.isInline())
1740 hasInlineChild = true;
1741
1742 if (o.isReplaced() || o.isFloating() || o.isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
1743 RenderBox& box = downcast<RenderBox>(o);
1744
1745 if (relayoutChildren || box.hasRelativeDimensions())
1746 box.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1747
1748 // If relayoutChildren is set and the child has percentage padding or an embedded content box, we also need to invalidate the childs pref widths.
1749 if (relayoutChildren && box.needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation())
1750 box.setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
1751
1752 if (box.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
1753 box.containingBlock()->insertPositionedObject(box);
1754 else if (box.isFloating())
1755 layoutState.floatList().append(FloatWithRect::create(box));
1756 else if (isFullLayout || box.needsLayout()) {
1757 // Replaced element.
1758 if (isFullLayout && is<RenderRubyRun>(box)) {
1759 // FIXME: This resets the overhanging margins that we set during line layout (see computeInlineDirectionPositionsForSegment)
1760 // Find a more suitable place for this.
1761 m_flow.setMarginStartForChild(box, 0);
1762 m_flow.setMarginEndForChild(box, 0);
1763 }
1764 box.dirtyLineBoxes(isFullLayout);
1765 if (isFullLayout)
1766 replacedChildren.append(&box);
1767 else
1768 box.layoutIfNeeded();
1769 }
1770 } else if (o.isTextOrLineBreak() || (is<RenderInline>(o) && !walker.atEndOfInline())) {
1771 if (is<RenderInline>(o))
1772 downcast<RenderInline>(o).updateAlwaysCreateLineBoxes(layoutState.isFullLayout());
1773 if (layoutState.isFullLayout() || o.selfNeedsLayout())
1774 dirtyLineBoxesForRenderer(o, layoutState.isFullLayout());
1775 o.clearNeedsLayout();
1776 }
1777 }
1778
1779 for (size_t i = 0; i < replacedChildren.size(); i++)
1780 replacedChildren[i]->layoutIfNeeded();
1781
1782 layoutRunsAndFloats(layoutState, hasInlineChild);
1783 }
1784
1785 // Expand the last line to accommodate Ruby and emphasis marks.
1786 int lastLineAnnotationsAdjustment = 0;
1787 if (lastRootBox()) {
1788 LayoutUnit lowestAllowedPosition = std::max(lastRootBox()->lineBottom(), m_flow.logicalHeight() + m_flow.paddingAfter());
1789 if (!style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode())
1790 lastLineAnnotationsAdjustment = lastRootBox()->computeUnderAnnotationAdjustment(lowestAllowedPosition);
1791 else
1792 lastLineAnnotationsAdjustment = lastRootBox()->computeOverAnnotationAdjustment(lowestAllowedPosition);
1793 }
1794
1795 // Now do the handling of the bottom of the block, adding in our bottom border/padding and
1796 // determining the correct collapsed bottom margin information. This collapse is only necessary
1797 // if our last child was an anonymous inline block that might need to propagate margin information out to
1798 // us.
1799 LayoutUnit afterEdge = m_flow.borderAndPaddingAfter() + m_flow.scrollbarLogicalHeight() + lastLineAnnotationsAdjustment;
1800 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(m_flow.logicalHeight() + afterEdge);
1801
1802 if (!firstRootBox() && m_flow.hasLineIfEmpty())
1803 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(m_flow.logicalHeight() + m_flow.lineHeight(true, m_flow.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes));
1804
1805 // See if we have any lines that spill out of our block. If we do, then we will possibly need to
1806 // truncate text.
1807 if (hasTextOverflow)
1808 checkLinesForTextOverflow();
1809}
1810
1811void LegacyLineLayout::checkFloatInCleanLine(LegacyRootInlineBox& cleanLine, RenderBox& floatBoxOnCleanLine, FloatWithRect& matchingFloatWithRect,
1812 bool& encounteredNewFloat, bool& dirtiedByFloat)
1813{
1814 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!floatBoxOnCleanLine.style().deletionHasBegun());
1815 if (&matchingFloatWithRect.renderer() != &floatBoxOnCleanLine) {
1816 encounteredNewFloat = true;
1817 return;
1818 }
1819 floatBoxOnCleanLine.layoutIfNeeded();
1820 LayoutRect originalFloatRect = matchingFloatWithRect.rect();
1821 LayoutSize newSize(
1822 floatBoxOnCleanLine.width() + floatBoxOnCleanLine.horizontalMarginExtent(),
1823 floatBoxOnCleanLine.height() + floatBoxOnCleanLine.verticalMarginExtent());
1824
1825 // We have to reset the cap-height alignment done by the first-letter floats when initial-letter is set, so just always treat first-letter floats as dirty.
1826 if (originalFloatRect.size() == newSize && (floatBoxOnCleanLine.style().styleType() != PseudoId::FirstLetter || !floatBoxOnCleanLine.style().initialLetterDrop()))
1827 return;
1828
1829 LayoutUnit floatTop = m_flow.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? originalFloatRect.y() : originalFloatRect.x();
1830 LayoutUnit floatHeight = m_flow.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? std::max(originalFloatRect.height(), newSize.height())
1831 : std::max(originalFloatRect.width(), newSize.width());
1832 floatHeight = std::min(floatHeight, LayoutUnit::max() - floatTop);
1833 cleanLine.markDirty();
1834 m_flow.markLinesDirtyInBlockRange(cleanLine.lineBoxBottom(), floatTop + floatHeight, &cleanLine);
1835 LayoutRect newFloatRect = originalFloatRect;
1836 newFloatRect.setSize(newSize);
1837 matchingFloatWithRect.adjustRect(newFloatRect);
1838 dirtiedByFloat = true;
1839}
1840
1841LegacyRootInlineBox* LegacyLineLayout::determineStartPosition(LineLayoutState& layoutState, InlineBidiResolver& resolver)
1842{
1843 LegacyRootInlineBox* currentLine = nullptr;
1844 LegacyRootInlineBox* lastLine = nullptr;
1845
1846 // FIXME: This entire float-checking block needs to be broken into a new function.
1847 auto& floats = layoutState.floatList();
1848 bool dirtiedByFloat = false;
1849 if (!layoutState.isFullLayout()) {
1850 // Paginate all of the clean lines.
1851 bool paginated = layoutContext().layoutState() && layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated();
1852 LayoutUnit paginationDelta;
1853 auto floatsIterator = floats.begin();
1854 auto end = floats.end();
1855 for (currentLine = firstRootBox(); currentLine && !currentLine->isDirty(); currentLine = currentLine->nextRootBox()) {
1856 if (paginated) {
1857 if (lineWidthForPaginatedLineChanged(currentLine, 0, layoutState.fragmentedFlow())) {
1858 currentLine->markDirty();
1859 break;
1860 }
1861 paginationDelta -= currentLine->paginationStrut();
1862 bool overflowsFragment;
1863 m_flow.adjustLinePositionForPagination(currentLine, paginationDelta, overflowsFragment, layoutState.fragmentedFlow());
1864 if (paginationDelta) {
1865 if (m_flow.containsFloats() || !floats.isEmpty()) {
1866 // FIXME: Do better eventually. For now if we ever shift because of pagination and floats are present just go to a full layout.
1867 layoutState.markForFullLayout();
1868 break;
1869 }
1870
1871 layoutState.updateRepaintRangeFromBox(currentLine, paginationDelta);
1872 currentLine->adjustBlockDirectionPosition(paginationDelta);
1873 }
1874 if (layoutState.fragmentedFlow())
1875 updateFragmentForLine(currentLine);
1876 }
1877
1878 if (auto* cleanLineFloats = currentLine->floatsPtr()) {
1879 // If a new float has been inserted before this line or before its last known float, just do a full layout.
1880 bool encounteredNewFloat = false;
1881 for (auto& floatBoxOnCleanLine : *cleanLineFloats) {
1882 ASSERT(floatsIterator != end);
1883 if (!floatBoxOnCleanLine)
1884 continue;
1885 checkFloatInCleanLine(*currentLine, *floatBoxOnCleanLine, *floatsIterator, encounteredNewFloat, dirtiedByFloat);
1886 ++floatsIterator;
1887 if (floatsIterator == end || encounteredNewFloat) {
1888 layoutState.markForFullLayout();
1889 break;
1890 }
1891 }
1892 if (dirtiedByFloat || encounteredNewFloat)
1893 break;
1894 }
1895 }
1896 // Check if a new float has been inserted after the last known float.
1897 if (floatsIterator != end) {
1898 if (!currentLine)
1899 layoutState.markForFullLayout();
1900 else {
1901 for (; floatsIterator != end; ++floatsIterator) {
1902 auto& floatWithRect = *floatsIterator;
1903 if (!floatWithRect->renderer().needsLayout())
1904 continue;
1905 layoutState.markForFullLayout();
1906 break;
1907 }
1908 }
1909 }
1910 }
1911
1912 if (layoutState.isFullLayout()) {
1913 m_lineBoxes.deleteLineBoxTree();
1914 currentLine = nullptr;
1915 ASSERT(!firstRootBox() && !lastRootBox());
1916 } else {
1917 if (currentLine) {
1918 // We have a dirty line.
1919 if (LegacyRootInlineBox* prevRootBox = currentLine->prevRootBox()) {
1920 // We have a previous line.
1921 if (!dirtiedByFloat && (!prevRootBox->endsWithBreak()
1922 || !prevRootBox->lineBreakObj()
1923 || (is<RenderText>(*prevRootBox->lineBreakObj())
1924 && prevRootBox->lineBreakPos() >= downcast<RenderText>(*prevRootBox->lineBreakObj()).text().length()))) {
1925 // The previous line didn't break cleanly or broke at a newline
1926 // that has been deleted, so treat it as dirty too.
1927 currentLine = prevRootBox;
1928 }
1929 }
1930 }
1931 // If we have no dirty lines, then last is just the last root box.
1932 lastLine = currentLine ? currentLine->prevRootBox() : lastRootBox();
1933 }
1934
1935 if (!floats.isEmpty()) {
1936 LayoutUnit savedLogicalHeight = m_flow.logicalHeight();
1937 // Restore floats from clean lines.
1938 LegacyRootInlineBox* line = firstRootBox();
1939 while (line != currentLine) {
1940 if (auto* cleanLineFloats = line->floatsPtr()) {
1941 for (auto& floatingBox : *cleanLineFloats) {
1942 if (!floatingBox)
1943 continue;
1944 auto* floatingObject = m_flow.insertFloatingObject(*floatingBox);
1945 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!floatingObject->originatingLine());
1946 floatingObject->setOriginatingLine(*line);
1947 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(m_flow.logicalTopForChild(*floatingBox) - m_flow.marginBeforeForChild(*floatingBox));
1948 m_flow.positionNewFloats();
1949 floats.setLastCleanFloat(*floatingBox);
1950 }
1951 }
1952 line = line->nextRootBox();
1953 }
1954 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(savedLogicalHeight);
1955 }
1956
1957 layoutState.lineInfo().setFirstLine(!lastLine);
1958 layoutState.lineInfo().setPreviousLineBrokeCleanly(!lastLine || lastLine->endsWithBreak());
1959
1960 if (lastLine) {
1961 m_flow.setLogicalHeight(lastLine->lineBoxBottom());
1962 InlineIterator iter = InlineIterator(&m_flow, lastLine->lineBreakObj(), lastLine->lineBreakPos());
1963 resolver.setPosition(iter, numberOfIsolateAncestors(iter));
1964 resolver.setStatus(lastLine->lineBreakBidiStatus());
1965 } else {
1966 TextDirection direction = style().direction();
1967 if (style().unicodeBidi() == Plaintext)
1968 determineDirectionality(direction, InlineIterator(&m_flow, bidiFirstSkippingEmptyInlines(m_flow), 0));
1969 resolver.setStatus(BidiStatus(direction, isOverride(style().unicodeBidi())));
1970 InlineIterator iter = InlineIterator(&m_flow, bidiFirstSkippingEmptyInlines(m_flow, &resolver), 0);
1971 resolver.setPosition(iter, numberOfIsolateAncestors(iter));
1972 }
1973 return currentLine;
1974}
1975
1976void LegacyLineLayout::determineEndPosition(LineLayoutState& layoutState, LegacyRootInlineBox* startLine, InlineIterator& cleanLineStart, BidiStatus& cleanLineBidiStatus)
1977{
1978 auto iteratorForFirstDirtyFloat = [](LineLayoutState::FloatList& floats) {
1979 auto lastCleanFloat = floats.lastCleanFloat();
1980 if (!lastCleanFloat)
1981 return floats.begin();
1982 auto* lastCleanFloatWithRect = floats.floatWithRect(*lastCleanFloat);
1983 ASSERT(lastCleanFloatWithRect);
1984 return ++floats.find(*lastCleanFloatWithRect);
1985 };
1986
1987 ASSERT(!layoutState.endLine());
1988 auto floatsIterator = iteratorForFirstDirtyFloat(layoutState.floatList());
1989 auto end = layoutState.floatList().end();
1990 LegacyRootInlineBox* lastLine = nullptr;
1991 for (auto* currentLine = startLine->nextRootBox(); currentLine; currentLine = currentLine->nextRootBox()) {
1992 if (!currentLine->isDirty()) {
1993 if (auto* cleanLineFloats = currentLine->floatsPtr()) {
1994 bool encounteredNewFloat = false;
1995 bool dirtiedByFloat = false;
1996 for (auto& floatBoxOnCleanLine : *cleanLineFloats) {
1997 if (!floatBoxOnCleanLine)
1998 continue;
1999 ASSERT(floatsIterator != end);
2000 checkFloatInCleanLine(*currentLine, *floatBoxOnCleanLine, *floatsIterator, encounteredNewFloat, dirtiedByFloat);
2001 ++floatsIterator;
2002 if (floatsIterator == end || encounteredNewFloat)
2003 return;
2004 }
2005 }
2006 }
2007 if (currentLine->isDirty())
2008 lastLine = nullptr;
2009 else if (!lastLine)
2010 lastLine = currentLine;
2011 }
2012
2013 if (!lastLine)
2014 return;
2015
2016 // At this point, |last| is the first line in a run of clean lines that ends with the last line
2017 // in the block.
2018 LegacyRootInlineBox* previousLine = lastLine->prevRootBox();
2019 cleanLineStart = InlineIterator(&m_flow, previousLine->lineBreakObj(), previousLine->lineBreakPos());
2020 cleanLineBidiStatus = previousLine->lineBreakBidiStatus();
2021 layoutState.setEndLineLogicalTop(previousLine->lineBoxBottom());
2022
2023 for (auto* line = lastLine; line; line = line->nextRootBox()) {
2024 // Disconnect all line boxes from their render objects while preserving their connections to one another.
2025 line->extractLine();
2026 }
2027 layoutState.setEndLine(lastLine);
2028}
2029
2030bool LegacyLineLayout::checkPaginationAndFloatsAtEndLine(LineLayoutState& layoutState)
2031{
2032 LayoutUnit lineDelta = m_flow.logicalHeight() - layoutState.endLineLogicalTop();
2033
2034 bool paginated = layoutContext().layoutState() && layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated();
2035 if (paginated && layoutState.fragmentedFlow()) {
2036 // Check all lines from here to the end, and see if the hypothetical new position for the lines will result
2037 // in a different available line width.
2038 for (auto* lineBox = layoutState.endLine(); lineBox; lineBox = lineBox->nextRootBox()) {
2039 if (paginated) {
2040 // This isn't the real move we're going to do, so don't update the line box's pagination
2041 // strut yet.
2042 LayoutUnit oldPaginationStrut = lineBox->paginationStrut();
2043 bool overflowsFragment;
2044 lineDelta -= oldPaginationStrut;
2045 m_flow.adjustLinePositionForPagination(lineBox, lineDelta, overflowsFragment, layoutState.fragmentedFlow());
2046 lineBox->setPaginationStrut(oldPaginationStrut);
2047 }
2048 if (lineWidthForPaginatedLineChanged(lineBox, lineDelta, layoutState.fragmentedFlow()))
2049 return false;
2050 }
2051 }
2052
2053 if (!lineDelta || !m_flow.floatingObjects())
2054 return true;
2055
2056 // See if any floats end in the range along which we want to shift the lines vertically.
2057 LayoutUnit logicalTop = std::min(m_flow.logicalHeight(), layoutState.endLineLogicalTop());
2058
2059 LegacyRootInlineBox* lastLine = layoutState.endLine();
2060 while (LegacyRootInlineBox* nextLine = lastLine->nextRootBox())
2061 lastLine = nextLine;
2062
2063 LayoutUnit logicalBottom = lastLine->lineBoxBottom() + absoluteValue(lineDelta);
2064
2065 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_flow.floatingObjects()->set();
2066 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
2067 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
2068 const auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
2069 if (m_flow.logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject) >= logicalTop && m_flow.logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject) < logicalBottom)
2070 return false;
2071 }
2072
2073 return true;
2074}
2075
2076bool LegacyLineLayout::lineWidthForPaginatedLineChanged(LegacyRootInlineBox* rootBox, LayoutUnit lineDelta, RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow) const
2077{
2078 if (!fragmentedFlow)
2079 return false;
2080
2081 RenderFragmentContainer* currentFragment = m_flow.fragmentAtBlockOffset(rootBox->lineBoxTop() + lineDelta);
2082 // Just bail if the fragment didn't change.
2083 if (rootBox->containingFragment() == currentFragment)
2084 return false;
2085 return rootBox->paginatedLineWidth() != m_flow.availableLogicalWidthForContent(currentFragment);
2086}
2087
2088bool LegacyLineLayout::matchedEndLine(LineLayoutState& layoutState, const InlineBidiResolver& resolver, const InlineIterator& endLineStart, const BidiStatus& endLineStatus)
2089{
2090 if (resolver.position() == endLineStart) {
2091 if (resolver.status() != endLineStatus)
2092 return false;
2093 return checkPaginationAndFloatsAtEndLine(layoutState);
2094 }
2095
2096 // The first clean line doesn't match, but we can check a handful of following lines to try
2097 // to match back up.
2098 static const int numLines = 8; // The # of lines we're willing to match against.
2099 LegacyRootInlineBox* originalEndLine = layoutState.endLine();
2100 LegacyRootInlineBox* line = originalEndLine;
2101 for (int i = 0; i < numLines && line; i++, line = line->nextRootBox()) {
2102 if (line->lineBreakObj() == resolver.position().renderer() && line->lineBreakPos() == resolver.position().offset()) {
2103 // We have a match.
2104 if (line->lineBreakBidiStatus() != resolver.status())
2105 return false; // ...but the bidi state doesn't match.
2106
2107 bool matched = false;
2108 LegacyRootInlineBox* result = line->nextRootBox();
2109 layoutState.setEndLine(result);
2110 if (result) {
2111 layoutState.setEndLineLogicalTop(line->lineBoxBottom());
2112 matched = checkPaginationAndFloatsAtEndLine(layoutState);
2113 }
2114
2115 // Now delete the lines that we failed to sync.
2116 deleteLineRange(layoutState, originalEndLine, result);
2117 return matched;
2118 }
2119 }
2120
2121 return false;
2122}
2123
2124void LegacyLineLayout::addOverflowFromInlineChildren()
2125{
2126 LayoutUnit endPadding = m_flow.hasOverflowClip() ? m_flow.paddingEnd() : 0_lu;
2127 // FIXME: Need to find another way to do this, since scrollbars could show when we don't want them to.
2128 if (!endPadding)
2129 endPadding = m_flow.endPaddingWidthForCaret();
2130 if (m_flow.hasOverflowClip() && !endPadding && m_flow.element() && m_flow.element()->isRootEditableElement() && style().isLeftToRightDirection())
2131 endPadding = 1;
2132 for (auto* curr = firstRootBox(); curr; curr = curr->nextRootBox()) {
2133 m_flow.addLayoutOverflow(curr->paddedLayoutOverflowRect(endPadding));
2134 RenderFragmentContainer* fragment = m_flow.enclosingFragmentedFlow() ? curr->containingFragment() : nullptr;
2135 if (fragment)
2136 fragment->addLayoutOverflowForBox(&m_flow, curr->paddedLayoutOverflowRect(endPadding));
2137 if (!m_flow.hasOverflowClip()) {
2138 LayoutRect childVisualOverflowRect = curr->visualOverflowRect(curr->lineTop(), curr->lineBottom());
2139 m_flow.addVisualOverflow(childVisualOverflowRect);
2140 if (fragment)
2141 fragment->addVisualOverflowForBox(&m_flow, childVisualOverflowRect);
2142 }
2143 }
2144}

2166
2167void LegacyLineLayout::deleteEllipsisLineBoxes()
2168{
2169 TextAlignMode textAlign = style().textAlign();
2170 bool ltr = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
2171 IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText = IndentText;
2172 for (auto* curr = firstRootBox(); curr; curr = curr->nextRootBox()) {
2173 if (curr->hasEllipsisBox()) {
2174 curr->clearTruncation();
2175
2176 // Shift the line back where it belongs if we cannot accomodate an ellipsis.
2177 float logicalLeft = m_flow.logicalLeftOffsetForLine(curr->lineTop(), shouldIndentText);
2178 float availableLogicalWidth = m_flow.logicalRightOffsetForLine(curr->lineTop(), DoNotIndentText) - logicalLeft;
2179 float totalLogicalWidth = curr->logicalWidth();
2180 updateLogicalWidthForAlignment(m_flow, textAlign, curr, 0, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, 0);
2181
2182 if (ltr)
2183 curr->adjustLogicalPosition((logicalLeft - curr->logicalLeft()), 0);
2184 else
2185 curr->adjustLogicalPosition(-(curr->logicalLeft() - logicalLeft), 0);
2186 }
2187 shouldIndentText = DoNotIndentText;
2188 }
2189}

2191void LegacyLineLayout::checkLinesForTextOverflow()
2192{
2193 // Determine the width of the ellipsis using the current font.
2194 // FIXME: CSS3 says this is configurable, also need to use 0x002E (FULL STOP) if horizontal ellipsis is "not renderable"
2195 const FontCascade& font = style().fontCascade();
2196 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> ellipsisStr(&horizontalEllipsis, 1);
2197 const FontCascade& firstLineFont = m_flow.firstLineStyle().fontCascade();
2198 float firstLineEllipsisWidth = firstLineFont.width(m_flow.constructTextRun(&horizontalEllipsis, 1, m_flow.firstLineStyle()));
2199 float ellipsisWidth = (font == firstLineFont) ? firstLineEllipsisWidth : font.width(m_flow.constructTextRun(&horizontalEllipsis, 1, style()));
2200
2201 // For LTR text truncation, we want to get the right edge of our padding box, and then we want to see
2202 // if the right edge of a line box exceeds that. For RTL, we use the left edge of the padding box and
2203 // check the left edge of the line box to see if it is less
2204 // Include the scrollbar for overflow blocks, which means we want to use "contentWidth()"
2205 bool ltr = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
2206 TextAlignMode textAlign = style().textAlign();
2207 bool firstLine = true;
2208 for (auto* curr = firstRootBox(); curr; curr = curr->nextRootBox()) {
2209 IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText = firstLine ? IndentText : DoNotIndentText;
2210 LayoutUnit blockRightEdge = m_flow.logicalRightOffsetForLine(curr->lineTop(), shouldIndentText);
2211 LayoutUnit blockLeftEdge = m_flow.logicalLeftOffsetForLine(curr->lineTop(), shouldIndentText);
2212 LayoutUnit lineBoxEdge { ltr ? curr->x() + curr->logicalWidth() : curr->x() };
2213 if ((ltr && lineBoxEdge > blockRightEdge) || (!ltr && lineBoxEdge < blockLeftEdge)) {
2214 // This line spills out of our box in the appropriate direction. Now we need to see if the line
2215 // can be truncated. In order for truncation to be possible, the line must have sufficient space to
2216 // accommodate our truncation string, and no replaced elements (images, tables) can overlap the ellipsis
2217 // space.
2218 LayoutUnit width { firstLine ? firstLineEllipsisWidth : ellipsisWidth };
2219 LayoutUnit blockEdge { ltr ? blockRightEdge : blockLeftEdge };
2220 if (curr->lineCanAccommodateEllipsis(ltr, blockEdge, lineBoxEdge, width)) {
2221 float totalLogicalWidth = curr->placeEllipsis(ellipsisStr, ltr, blockLeftEdge, blockRightEdge, width);
2222
2223 float logicalLeft = 0; // We are only interested in the delta from the base position.
2224 float truncatedWidth = m_flow.availableLogicalWidthForLine(curr->lineTop(), shouldIndentText);
2225 updateLogicalWidthForAlignment(m_flow, textAlign, curr, nullptr, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, truncatedWidth, 0);
2226 if (ltr)
2227 curr->adjustLogicalPosition(logicalLeft, 0);
2228 else
2229 curr->adjustLogicalPosition(-(truncatedWidth - (logicalLeft + totalLogicalWidth)), 0);
2230 }
2231 }
2232 firstLine = false;
2233 }
2234}

2236bool LegacyLineLayout::positionNewFloatOnLine(const FloatingObject& newFloat, FloatingObject* lastFloatFromPreviousLine, LineInfo& lineInfo, LineWidth& width)
2237{
2238 if (!m_flow.positionNewFloats())
2239 return false;
2240
2241 width.shrinkAvailableWidthForNewFloatIfNeeded(newFloat);
2242
2243 // We only connect floats to lines for pagination purposes if the floats occur at the start of
2244 // the line and the previous line had a hard break (so this line is either the first in the block
2245 // or follows a <br>).
2246 if (!newFloat.paginationStrut() || !lineInfo.previousLineBrokeCleanly() || !lineInfo.isEmpty())
2247 return true;
2248
2249 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_flow.floatingObjects()->set();
2250 ASSERT(floatingObjectSet.last().get() == &newFloat);
2251
2252 LayoutUnit floatLogicalTop = m_flow.logicalTopForFloat(newFloat);
2253 LayoutUnit paginationStrut = newFloat.paginationStrut();
2254
2255 if (floatLogicalTop - paginationStrut != m_flow.logicalHeight() + lineInfo.floatPaginationStrut())
2256 return true;
2257
2258 auto it = floatingObjectSet.end();
2259 --it; // Last float is newFloat, skip that one.
2260 auto begin = floatingObjectSet.begin();
2261 while (it != begin) {
2262 --it;
2263 auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
2264 if (&floatingObject == lastFloatFromPreviousLine)
2265 break;
2266 if (m_flow.logicalTopForFloat(floatingObject) == m_flow.logicalHeight() + lineInfo.floatPaginationStrut()) {
2267 floatingObject.setPaginationStrut(paginationStrut + floatingObject.paginationStrut());
2268 RenderBox& floatBox = floatingObject.renderer();
2269 m_flow.setLogicalTopForChild(floatBox, m_flow.logicalTopForChild(floatBox) + m_flow.marginBeforeForChild(floatBox) + paginationStrut);
2270
2271 if (m_flow.updateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(floatBox))
2272 floatBox.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2273 else if (is<RenderBlock>(floatBox))
2274 downcast<RenderBlock>(floatBox).setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2275 floatBox.layoutIfNeeded();
2276
2277 // Save the old logical top before calling removePlacedObject which will set
2278 // isPlaced to false. Otherwise it will trigger an assert in logicalTopForFloat.
2279 LayoutUnit oldLogicalTop = m_flow.logicalTopForFloat(floatingObject);
2280 m_flow.floatingObjects()->removePlacedObject(&floatingObject);
2281 m_flow.setLogicalTopForFloat(floatingObject, oldLogicalTop + paginationStrut);
2282 m_flow.floatingObjects()->addPlacedObject(&floatingObject);
2283 }
2284 }
2285
2286 // Just update the line info's pagination strut without altering our logical height yet. If the line ends up containing
2287 // no content, then we don't want to improperly grow the height of the block.
2288 lineInfo.setFloatPaginationStrut(lineInfo.floatPaginationStrut() + paginationStrut);
2289 return true;

2292void LegacyLineLayout::updateFragmentForLine(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox) const
2293{
2294 ASSERT(lineBox);
2295
2296 if (!m_flow.hasFragmentRangeInFragmentedFlow())
2297 lineBox->clearContainingFragment();
2298 else {
2299 if (auto containingFragment = m_flow.fragmentAtBlockOffset(lineBox->lineBoxTop()))
2300 lineBox->setContainingFragment(*containingFragment);
2301 else
2302 lineBox->clearContainingFragment();
2303 }

2305 LegacyRootInlineBox* prevLineBox = lineBox->prevRootBox();

2307 return;

2309 // This check is more accurate than the one in |adjustLinePositionForPagination| because it takes into
2310 // account just the container changes between lines. The before mentioned function doesn't set the flag
2311 // correctly if the line is positioned at the top of the last fragment container.
2312 if (lineBox->containingFragment() != prevLineBox->containingFragment())
2313 lineBox->setIsFirstAfterPageBreak(true);
